WEBVTT

1
00:00:38.082 --> 00:00:41.710
We'll arrive in 20 minutes.
The donor is in good state.

2
00:00:41.835 --> 00:00:43.420
Hello? Hello?

3
00:00:44.421 --> 00:00:46.674
Power went out again?

4
00:00:58.060 --> 00:01:01.188
The papers check out.
The donor committed suicide.

5
00:01:01.313 --> 00:01:03.440
Why at such a young age?

6
00:01:03.566 --> 00:01:06.235
I know.
-Where's Dr. Oh? Dr. Oh!

7
00:01:06.360 --> 00:01:08.194
Right here.
-Jesus!

8
00:01:08.320 --> 00:01:10.279
Hello. sir!
-What's the status?

9
00:01:10.406 --> 00:01:12.157
We must start the extraction.

10
00:01:12.950 --> 00:01:16.244
What's that?
A birthmark or a tattoo?

11
00:01:16.370 --> 00:01:17.830
Tattoo.

12
00:01:19.290 --> 00:01:22.209
He looks familiar.
-I think I saw him too.

13
00:01:22.918 --> 00:01:25.628
Maybe in a history book?

14
00:01:25.754 --> 00:01:28.090
Pay tribute.
Loved and missed by someone....

15
00:01:28.215 --> 00:01:32.803
...the donor sprinkled
flowers of love and left this land.

16
00:01:37.391 --> 00:01:38.934
My arm hurts.

17
00:01:39.059 --> 00:01:41.979
His body is like steel.
How many knives did we break?

18
00:01:42.438 --> 00:01:44.189
What is he. a superhero
or something?

19
00:01:45.065 --> 00:01:48.444
Jesus Christ!
-What? What's wrong?

20
00:01:48.569 --> 00:01:51.030
Monster!
-A mouse?

21
00:01:53.073 --> 00:01:54.783
Come out!
-Don't come!

22
00:01:54.908 --> 00:01:57.453
Come out!
-Don't come out! Hurry!

23
00:01:57.911 --> 00:01:59.371
Water!

24
00:03:40.723 --> 00:03:42.266
You're not sick at all?
-No.

25
00:03:42.391 --> 00:03:43.976
How many times
must I say that?

26
00:03:44.101 --> 00:03:45.561
Normally. that's impossible.

27
00:03:45.686 --> 00:03:48.939
You should throw up.
drool. and such.

28
00:03:49.064 --> 00:03:50.524
With someone else's heart
transplanted....

29
00:03:50.649 --> 00:03:54.611
...you're healed right away?
That's odd.

30
00:03:54.737 --> 00:03:56.697
If she's not sick. isn't that good?
-Of course.

31
00:03:56.822 --> 00:03:58.282
I'm glad she's fine....

32
00:03:58.407 --> 00:04:00.242
...but I wonder if there is
something else going on.

33
00:04:00.367 --> 00:04:02.161
So. can I go home or not?

34
00:04:03.370 --> 00:04:05.080
If you're fine. you can.

35
00:04:07.124 --> 00:04:09.626
What's that?
Did you get a tattoo?

36
00:04:10.919 --> 00:04:14.423
I don't know. Maybe it's
a side effect from the surgery.

37
00:04:14.548 --> 00:04:16.341
Did you make a bad friend
in the hospital?

38
00:04:16.467 --> 00:04:19.720
I don't have any friends!
-Don't yell and eat slowly.

39
00:04:19.845 --> 00:04:21.638
See? Your heart rate is over 90!

40
00:04:21.764 --> 00:04:23.223
Come on. Dad.

41
00:04:23.682 --> 00:04:26.351
Don't buy expensive stuff
like this. You have no money.

42
00:04:26.518 --> 00:04:28.145
Who says I have no money?

43
00:04:28.312 --> 00:04:30.272
If there's anything you want
to do or buy. just say it.

44
00:04:30.397 --> 00:04:31.857
I want to do something.
-Say it.

45
00:04:31.982 --> 00:04:33.650
Start up Taekwondo again.
-No way.

46
00:04:33.776 --> 00:04:35.486
You said to say what I want!
-Not Taekwondo. Never!

47
00:04:35.611 --> 00:04:37.446
It's dangerous.
-Doc said I can run moderately.

48
00:04:37.571 --> 00:04:39.907
What does he know? Dad knows best.
-Why get me a heart transplant...

49
00:04:40.032 --> 00:04:42.284
...if I can't even run?
-You can do Pilates...

50
00:04:42.409 --> 00:04:44.244
...when you go to college.
-Dad!

51
00:04:44.369 --> 00:04:45.829
Listen!

52
00:04:47.121 --> 00:04:49.625
When I think of your heart attack
at the competition....

53
00:04:49.750 --> 00:04:51.210
...I get cold sweats.

54
00:04:52.419 --> 00:04:53.879
Your mom.....

55
00:04:54.338 --> 00:04:56.423
She died from a heart attack.

56
00:04:57.007 --> 00:04:59.384
Your grandfather died
from a heart attack.

57
00:05:00.636 --> 00:05:06.933
If I lose you. too. I can't
live in this dreadful world!

58
00:05:10.437 --> 00:05:13.314
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected.

59
00:05:13.440 --> 00:05:16.401
Forever immortal.
transcendent body.

60
00:05:16.527 --> 00:05:20.739
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected.

61
00:05:20.864 --> 00:05:23.659
Forever immortal.
transcendent body.

62
00:05:23.784 --> 00:05:25.536
Yes. Lord.

63
00:05:25.701 --> 00:05:27.538
I know.

64
00:05:27.663 --> 00:05:30.958
Organs are not batteries.
but he keeps changing them.

65
00:05:31.958 --> 00:05:33.919
It's the pancreas this time.

66
00:05:34.962 --> 00:05:38.339
Fortunately. I think Dad
will not make it this time.

67
00:05:40.384 --> 00:05:42.219
Anyway....

68
00:05:42.344 --> 00:05:45.264
...you'll get everything
before the revival.

69
00:05:45.389 --> 00:05:47.516
Don't cut the price.

70
00:05:50.060 --> 00:05:51.728
Forever immortal.
transcendent body!

71
00:05:51.854 --> 00:05:53.522
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected!

72
00:05:53.647 --> 00:05:55.190
Forever immortal.
transcendent body!

73
00:05:55.315 --> 00:05:57.108
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected!

74
00:05:57.568 --> 00:06:00.236
I'm hungry.
Bring me some grilled meat.

75
00:06:00.362 --> 00:06:01.822
Forever immortal.
transcendent body!

76
00:06:05.409 --> 00:06:07.285
Add more power!

77
00:06:07.410 --> 00:06:08.912
Let's take on the world!

78
00:06:15.210 --> 00:06:16.670
Dad.
-No way.

79
00:06:16.794 --> 00:06:18.672
I didn't even ask.
-You can't do Taekwondo.

80
00:06:18.839 --> 00:06:20.340
That's not it.

81
00:06:20.465 --> 00:06:22.591
Did you run during gym?
I saw your heart rate go up.

82
00:06:22.718 --> 00:06:25.136
Rendezvous!
-I didn't run.

83
00:06:25.261 --> 00:06:27.264
Then what's with your shoes?
One more time!

84
00:06:27.389 --> 00:06:31.226
Come on. Stop it or I'll
just chuck this in the trash!

85
00:06:33.145 --> 00:06:37.733
Listen.
I'll be out driving tonight.

86
00:06:37.858 --> 00:06:41.486
Buy new shoes and go home.

87
00:06:41.612 --> 00:06:43.780
Buy healthy food
with your friends. too.

88
00:06:43.906 --> 00:06:45.365
Class is over!

89
00:06:45.490 --> 00:06:46.950
Courtesy and courage!
-I don't have friends.

90
00:06:47.075 --> 00:06:48.994
Taekwondo!
Well done!

91
00:06:49.119 --> 00:06:52.539
Joong-pil! Do 50 kicks
as a penalty for being late.

92
00:06:53.582 --> 00:06:56.168
Taekwondo!
Sir! I was about to call...

93
00:06:56.293 --> 00:06:58.879
...and explain why
there is $100 missing.

94
00:06:59.004 --> 00:07:00.756
Hey. kid!

95
00:07:00.881 --> 00:07:04.551
Can't you kick better than that?

96
00:07:04.676 --> 00:07:07.846
I could do 540-degree kicks
at your age.

97
00:07:07.971 --> 00:07:10.724
Move.
This is all for your own good.

98
00:07:11.516 --> 00:07:15.812
Stand firm.
stare at the target. then kick!

99
00:07:20.776 --> 00:07:22.235
Joong-pil.
Say you did this. okay?

100
00:07:22.361 --> 00:07:23.820
What happened?

101
00:07:27.366 --> 00:07:31.745
Dad. We have a kid
here who will make it big!

102
00:07:31.870 --> 00:07:33.330
Taekwondo!

103
00:07:33.455 --> 00:07:36.667
Hey! Get her! Hurry!

104
00:07:36.917 --> 00:07:38.543
I'm sorry!
-Hurry up!

105
00:07:38.669 --> 00:07:41.380
I gotcha!
-I got you!

106
00:07:41.505 --> 00:07:43.715
You're slow!
-No way!

107
00:07:51.139 --> 00:07:53.141
"DAD:
DON'T RUN WITH YOUR FRIENDS!"

108
00:09:51.134 --> 00:09:53.470
Dr. Song said. fatty food
is bad for the pancreas.

109
00:09:53.595 --> 00:09:55.055
Say. ah!

110
00:09:57.682 --> 00:09:59.183
Choon-hwa.
-Yes. Dad.

111
00:09:59.308 --> 00:10:02.104
It must've been hard
to take care of me all this time.

112
00:10:02.229 --> 00:10:04.106
I'm sorry.
-Don't be.

113
00:10:04.231 --> 00:10:07.275
You need to be healthy
to bless the followers.

114
00:10:07.400 --> 00:10:09.528
You have to live
for all creation to.....

115
00:10:11.029 --> 00:10:13.406
Know what's amazing about humans?

116
00:10:14.157 --> 00:10:17.244
Even if you're in a coma
with a respirator on....

117
00:10:17.828 --> 00:10:20.122
...you can still hear well.

118
00:10:20.247 --> 00:10:22.582
When my dad was in a coma....

119
00:10:22.707 --> 00:10:25.168
...I said all kinds
of bad things about him.

120
00:10:25.418 --> 00:10:28.672
Jeez! He must've heard everything.

121
00:10:28.797 --> 00:10:30.257
I must admit....

122
00:10:30.423 --> 00:10:32.968
...I'm the worst jerk
in the world.

123
00:10:36.263 --> 00:10:41.226
It's like the engine and parts
were changed in car...

124
00:10:41.351 --> 00:10:43.478
...to a sports car.

125
00:10:43.603 --> 00:10:45.689
Just from getting a new pancreas?

126
00:10:46.731 --> 00:10:48.190
Then I should do it too.

127
00:10:48.315 --> 00:10:49.818
My guess is...

128
00:10:50.694 --> 00:10:57.200
...that the donor
had an unusual body type.

129
00:10:57.909 --> 00:11:02.164
Like the donor
had superpowers or something?

130
00:11:03.038 --> 00:11:05.417
"ALL ABOUT SUPERPOWERS." "HOW
TO WRITE SUCCESSFUL SCREENPLAYS"

131
00:11:19.597 --> 00:11:22.767
I said no Taekwondo!
Why keep wearing your uniform?

132
00:11:22.893 --> 00:11:24.394
It's comfortable.

133
00:11:24.519 --> 00:11:27.314
Doc said it's good for the heart
to wear comfortable clothes.

134
00:11:27.439 --> 00:11:29.357
Still! No Taekwondo for you!

135
00:11:29.524 --> 00:11:32.402
Don't run! Walk slowly!
-Okay. okay!

136
00:12:05.018 --> 00:12:08.396
You've been roaming around
our gym since last week.

137
00:12:08.521 --> 00:12:11.607
Are you a flasher. stalker.
or in love with me?

138
00:12:11.732 --> 00:12:14.819
All three are crimes!
-My arm! Ow!

139
00:12:15.528 --> 00:12:18.113
My arm!

140
00:12:21.576 --> 00:12:23.370
You're really strong.

141
00:12:23.495 --> 00:12:24.955
I should get this checked out.

142
00:12:25.080 --> 00:12:28.458
Come on! It was just a pinch
from a middle school girl. man!

143
00:12:28.583 --> 00:12:30.168
Why does a middle school girl
talk so tough?

144
00:12:30.293 --> 00:12:32.711
My grandfather raised me
when I was learning to speak.

145
00:12:33.255 --> 00:12:35.215
You don't know
what you're capable of. do you?

146
00:12:35.340 --> 00:12:39.970
I thought I had a sudden growth
spurt. No idea I had superpowers.

147
00:12:40.095 --> 00:12:42.055
Does your mom know?
-I don't have a mom.

148
00:12:43.223 --> 00:12:44.683
Do you have a dad?

149
00:12:45.350 --> 00:12:47.059
Yes. I do.
If he finds out....

150
00:12:47.184 --> 00:12:50.437
...he'll faint and cry like crazy
for 3 days.

151
00:12:50.563 --> 00:12:52.899
No way I can tell him.
-Good.

152
00:12:54.067 --> 00:12:55.902
It's a rule to keep
superpowers a secret.

153
00:12:56.027 --> 00:12:58.488
What superpower did you get.
Mister?

154
00:13:24.806 --> 00:13:27.267
Who's the donor
that we got the superpowers?

155
00:13:27.392 --> 00:13:29.185
Did you know six organs
can be donated?

156
00:13:29.352 --> 00:13:30.854
No.
-Heart. lungs....

157
00:13:30.979 --> 00:13:33.189
...cornea. kidney. liver.
and pancreas.

158
00:13:33.315 --> 00:13:35.525
It means there are
4 others besides us.

159
00:13:35.650 --> 00:13:37.319
Finding the rest of the recipients
should give us...

160
00:13:37.444 --> 00:13:39.112
...more clues.
-How do we find them?

161
00:13:39.237 --> 00:13:42.532
The 17th Transplant Recipients'
Sportsfest...

162
00:13:42.657 --> 00:13:45.744
...will be held at Seoul Park
on the 10th.

163
00:13:45.869 --> 00:13:49.497
The sporting event is held
every 2 years.

164
00:13:49.622 --> 00:13:52.375
Over 100 transplant receivers
are expected...

165
00:13:52.500 --> 00:13:55.253
...to take part this year.

166
00:13:55.378 --> 00:13:58.840
Chairman Hwang
of the association is.....

167
00:14:35.043 --> 00:14:36.544
"GOLD PARADISE GAME LAND"

168
00:15:01.027 --> 00:15:03.655
"THE 17th TRANSPLANT
RECIPIENTS' SPORTSFEST"

169
00:15:03.780 --> 00:15:06.116
Now. they're running fast!
They exchanged the batons!

170
00:15:06.241 --> 00:15:08.660
Well done!
Cornea team is winning!

171
00:15:08.785 --> 00:15:10.787
Heart team! Come on!

172
00:15:10.912 --> 00:15:12.705
You're in last place!

173
00:15:28.346 --> 00:15:30.306
Nike! Yes!

174
00:15:30.432 --> 00:15:32.434
I needed new shoes.

175
00:15:35.520 --> 00:15:37.439
Did you find them?
-Huh?

176
00:15:38.231 --> 00:15:40.942
No. they're not here.
Take it back.

177
00:15:41.067 --> 00:15:45.155
Why didn't you look harder instead
of staring at your phone all day?

178
00:15:45.780 --> 00:15:47.699
You don't have friends. do you?

179
00:15:47.824 --> 00:15:50.702
Why do I need friends?
-Have a drink!

180
00:15:51.953 --> 00:15:55.540
It's free.
I got a kidney transplant.

181
00:15:55.665 --> 00:15:59.043
I'm so healthy and thankful.
I'm giving this to everyone.

182
00:16:00.462 --> 00:16:03.423
It's good for digestion.
-Thank you.

183
00:16:04.048 --> 00:16:06.885
What else is there?
-If you can't digest well....

184
00:16:07.010 --> 00:16:09.679
...this has prebiotics
and probiotics.

185
00:16:09.804 --> 00:16:11.639
It'll coat your gut...

186
00:16:12.140 --> 00:16:14.684
...with vitamins and vegetables.
-Can I see your arm?

187
00:16:15.185 --> 00:16:16.644
My arm?

188
00:16:17.687 --> 00:16:19.230
Why?

189
00:16:20.023 --> 00:16:21.483
Other arm. too.

190
00:16:22.192 --> 00:16:23.651
For what?

191
00:16:23.985 --> 00:16:26.070
Do you have apple flavor?
-Of course!

192
00:16:26.196 --> 00:16:28.823
If you drink too much.
you'll get a stomach ache.

193
00:16:28.948 --> 00:16:31.075
We have some food and salad too.

194
00:16:31.201 --> 00:16:33.036
5% off on salads
with a delivery subscription.

195
00:16:33.161 --> 00:16:34.787
Let me show you.

196
00:16:34.913 --> 00:16:36.498
What are you doing?

197
00:16:36.623 --> 00:16:39.292
For me. after I got
a heart transplant....

198
00:16:39.417 --> 00:16:41.419
...I can run really fast.

199
00:16:41.544 --> 00:16:44.172
And see?
I got stronger.

200
00:16:44.339 --> 00:16:47.175
He got a lung transplant.

201
00:16:47.425 --> 00:16:48.885
Show her.

202
00:17:03.566 --> 00:17:05.026
What the heck!

203
00:17:07.153 --> 00:17:08.947
Come quick!

204
00:17:09.155 --> 00:17:12.742
What happened?
-What superpower do you have?

205
00:17:12.867 --> 00:17:14.327
Me?

206
00:17:15.411 --> 00:17:16.871
I don't have one.

207
00:17:17.539 --> 00:17:19.374
Nothing changed after your surgery?

208
00:17:19.499 --> 00:17:23.419
I'm not sure. but people say
my skin has improved.

209
00:17:23.545 --> 00:17:25.380
They say I'm prettier now.

210
00:17:25.505 --> 00:17:28.466
It's awkward to hear
that I'm so pretty.

211
00:17:30.385 --> 00:17:32.512
Is becoming prettier my superpower?

212
00:17:32.637 --> 00:17:34.097
Being pretty has power. right?

213
00:17:34.222 --> 00:17:36.683
You wish.
-I'm serious!

214
00:17:36.808 --> 00:17:40.478
Men come to buy yogurt.
then ask for my number saying....

215
00:17:40.603 --> 00:17:42.063
...I remind them
of their first love.

216
00:17:42.188 --> 00:17:44.065
Doubt it.
-Enjoy your meal.

217
00:17:46.693 --> 00:17:48.570
You have a tattoo. too.

218
00:17:48.695 --> 00:17:52.865
Then you must have a superpower.
but haven't discovered it yet.

219
00:17:52.991 --> 00:17:55.785
He's a whiz at superpowers.
He knows everything.

220
00:17:55.910 --> 00:17:58.288
When the superpowers
come together....

221
00:17:58.413 --> 00:18:00.665
...unknown. greater powers
may be released.

222
00:18:00.790 --> 00:18:02.375
We'll know more
when we find the others.

223
00:18:02.500 --> 00:18:03.960
How do we find them?

224
00:18:14.220 --> 00:18:17.015
Park Wan-seo.
Heart transplant.

225
00:18:17.139 --> 00:18:19.183
Jindeok Middle School.
grade 9 class 2.

226
00:18:19.309 --> 00:18:23.688
Taekwondo athlete.
Wow! Won 5 medals?

227
00:18:23.813 --> 00:18:26.190
Future goal.
To marry Doh Kyung-soo.

228
00:18:26.316 --> 00:18:29.109
Is he in BTS?
-No. EXO.

229
00:18:29.485 --> 00:18:30.987
Kim Seon-nyeo.
Kidney transplant.

230
00:18:31.112 --> 00:18:32.905
Born in 1975?

231
00:18:33.030 --> 00:18:34.532
Still single?

232
00:18:34.657 --> 00:18:36.868
You still look young
and pretty.

233
00:18:40.955 --> 00:18:43.666
Park Ji-sung.
Lung transplant.

234
00:18:45.335 --> 00:18:47.211
Job.....
-Stop!

235
00:18:48.254 --> 00:18:50.298
Who are you?
-I'm Hwang Ki-dong.

236
00:18:50.423 --> 00:18:53.426
A.k.a. the conductor.

237
00:18:53.551 --> 00:18:55.011
I got corneas.

238
00:19:00.767 --> 00:19:03.268
Ki-dong.
How'd you find us?

239
00:19:05.146 --> 00:19:07.899
You all have tattoos. right?

240
00:19:08.024 --> 00:19:09.942
If I come within a few meters....

241
00:19:10.068 --> 00:19:13.279
...it shines really brightly.

242
00:19:15.323 --> 00:19:18.116
Only I can see it.
I can't explain it.

243
00:19:18.409 --> 00:19:23.039
What you did before. was that like
controlling electricity or wi-fi?

244
00:19:23.956 --> 00:19:25.415
You mean this?

245
00:19:28.127 --> 00:19:29.586
Yes?

246
00:19:30.963 --> 00:19:33.841
One more beer. please.
-Sure.

247
00:19:37.136 --> 00:19:40.264
You're amazing.
Will you be the leader of our team?

248
00:19:40.390 --> 00:19:42.058
We'll find the others.....
-What leader?

249
00:19:42.850 --> 00:19:44.310
Is this a military regime?

250
00:19:45.603 --> 00:19:49.190
He can only tell within a few
meters. They could be anywhere.

251
00:19:49.315 --> 00:19:51.109
How about hacking like back then?

252
00:19:51.233 --> 00:19:53.361
In movies.....
-Hacking? Is this a dictatorship?

253
00:19:54.654 --> 00:19:57.782
If you get caught keeping tabs
on civilians. you'll be charged...

254
00:19:57.907 --> 00:20:00.201
...for violations in
privacy. communications act....

255
00:20:00.326 --> 00:20:03.037
...personal information sharing.
and defamation.

256
00:20:03.204 --> 00:20:05.957
You wanted to find
the others first.

257
00:20:06.081 --> 00:20:08.126
I'm saying
it's not a righteous way to do it.

258
00:20:08.251 --> 00:20:09.961
Can't be bothered?
-It's because I'm busy.

259
00:20:10.086 --> 00:20:11.546
But you don't have a job.

260
00:20:15.174 --> 00:20:16.718
Says who?
-Then what's your job?

261
00:20:16.843 --> 00:20:18.511
I write screenplays.

262
00:20:18.636 --> 00:20:20.096
What do you write?

263
00:20:21.639 --> 00:20:23.099
Hero stories.
-Let's see.

264
00:20:23.224 --> 00:20:26.269
It'll be done next week.
-You like hero stories?

265
00:20:26.477 --> 00:20:29.313
Then do you know Uriggiri?

266
00:20:29.772 --> 00:20:31.441
They have lots of stuff
on heroes.

267
00:20:31.566 --> 00:20:33.526
You like that site?
-Yes.

268
00:20:33.651 --> 00:20:36.904
That site is full of pro-japs.

269
00:20:37.029 --> 00:20:39.741
Are you a far-rightist?
-You must be a commie.

270
00:20:39.866 --> 00:20:42.034
I thought so.
Let's avoid talking.

271
00:20:42.160 --> 00:20:44.036
Are you talking down to me?
What year were you born?

272
00:20:44.161 --> 00:20:45.621
'88.
-I was born in '87.

273
00:20:45.747 --> 00:20:47.206
Early '88.
-What month?

274
00:20:47.331 --> 00:20:48.791
Early April.
-April '88?

275
00:20:48.916 --> 00:20:51.960
I'm almost a year older!
-So what if I'm a year younger?

276
00:20:52.128 --> 00:20:53.588
Respect me if
you're a year younger!

277
00:20:53.713 --> 00:20:56.507
Calm down. please!

278
00:20:56.673 --> 00:20:59.594
We got new lives from one donor.
We're like family!

279
00:21:09.228 --> 00:21:10.897
Hey. Mister!

280
00:21:11.481 --> 00:21:13.149
You said we'd split the bill!

281
00:21:15.442 --> 00:21:18.696
What is all this?

282
00:21:18.820 --> 00:21:21.324
What kind of show
will he put on this time...

283
00:21:21.449 --> 00:21:25.828
...to get the poor souls
to offer their skin and bones?

284
00:21:27.789 --> 00:21:31.751
Don't say it's too expensive now.
I'll just sell to someone else.

285
00:21:32.626 --> 00:21:35.880
You know cults are
booming in Korea.

286
00:22:28.808 --> 00:22:30.309
How annoying.....

287
00:22:32.186 --> 00:22:33.645
Get out.

288
00:22:34.814 --> 00:22:39.109
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected!

289
00:22:39.485 --> 00:22:41.779
God of heaven and earth.
Lord Jae-lim.

290
00:22:41.904 --> 00:22:44.365
Congratulations on your return.

291
00:22:44.490 --> 00:22:46.701
Thank you for coming. Lord Jae-lim.

292
00:22:46.826 --> 00:22:49.996
How can I save more helpless souls?

293
00:22:50.829 --> 00:22:52.540
I should learn from you.

294
00:22:52.664 --> 00:22:56.544
It sounds like you've come
to steal them from me.

295
00:22:56.961 --> 00:22:58.963
It must be from hurting your ear.

296
00:22:59.881 --> 00:23:01.382
You've heard wrong. sir.

297
00:23:01.507 --> 00:23:03.426
No. no.

298
00:23:03.593 --> 00:23:05.386
I can hear well.

299
00:23:10.892 --> 00:23:14.645
How much did my daughter want
for handing over the foundation?

300
00:23:15.730 --> 00:23:19.942
Still. she wouldn't sell the
pharmaceutical company...

301
00:23:20.067 --> 00:23:23.571
...because you started out
with that business.

302
00:23:24.447 --> 00:23:26.281
She's a dutiful daughter.

303
00:23:26.823 --> 00:23:28.284
Byung-choon.

304
00:23:28.993 --> 00:23:31.829
There are no good.
dutiful kids in our family.

305
00:23:32.371 --> 00:23:34.165
We're greedy by blood.

306
00:23:34.290 --> 00:23:37.835
She wanted $450 per follower.

307
00:23:38.127 --> 00:23:41.130
I'll pay $500 if you hand them over
before the revival.

308
00:23:41.255 --> 00:23:44.675
I hurt my ear because of you.
remember?

309
00:23:44.967 --> 00:23:48.054
You hit it by mistake
during our strength demo.

310
00:23:48.178 --> 00:23:51.182
$550!
-So I beat you to a pulp...

311
00:23:51.390 --> 00:23:54.393
...and you pooed in your pants.

312
00:23:55.394 --> 00:23:59.190
I sold lots of pills that day.
-That's enough. sir!

313
00:23:59.315 --> 00:24:01.733
You're a pants-pooper
who tailed a medicine peddler!

314
00:24:01.859 --> 00:24:04.487
Think you've become a god?

315
00:24:04.611 --> 00:24:07.531
I said stop it!
Darn peddler!

316
00:24:07.657 --> 00:24:10.617
Don't call me a pants-pooper!

317
00:24:10.743 --> 00:24:12.203
It's the truth!

318
00:25:24.859 --> 00:25:27.403
Good! That's it!

319
00:25:27.528 --> 00:25:30.322
5 minutes left on the lunch break!

320
00:25:31.532 --> 00:25:36.203
We must take positions now
to start work on time.

321
00:25:36.746 --> 00:25:40.082
Right timing keeps us safe.
Please wear your hard hats.

322
00:25:40.750 --> 00:25:42.375
There are 3 minutes left!

323
00:25:43.377 --> 00:25:46.380
Employers cannot force
overtime work.

324
00:25:46.505 --> 00:25:49.759
Do you know this is a violation
of the Labor Act?

325
00:25:49.884 --> 00:25:51.635
If you know the law well.
Seung-hoon....

326
00:25:51.759 --> 00:25:53.554
...why are you working here?

327
00:25:53.679 --> 00:25:55.639
Please don't discriminate
against contract workers.

328
00:25:55.765 --> 00:26:00.186
I'm not. I know we must keep
to the break time and work time.

329
00:26:00.311 --> 00:26:02.730
But the foundation
doesn't stick to the rules.

330
00:26:02.855 --> 00:26:06.942
We're lacking safety equipment
and do more work for the revival.

331
00:26:07.068 --> 00:26:09.361
If there's an accident.
will you save everyone. chief?

332
00:26:09.487 --> 00:26:11.530
Think the cult leader will?
-An unsaved man...

333
00:26:11.655 --> 00:26:15.117
...who will fall in hell! How dare
you bad-mouth the New Father God!

334
00:26:27.880 --> 00:26:30.132
What happened?
-It fell from up there.

335
00:26:30.257 --> 00:26:34.595
Darn it! I asked that to be
replaced a dozen times!

336
00:26:35.304 --> 00:26:36.764
Call emergency!

337
00:27:08.504 --> 00:27:11.507
When are they coming?
-Choi called them.

338
00:27:37.116 --> 00:27:43.747
"PUTTING SAFETY FIRST
MAKES YOU A SUPERHERO!"

339
00:27:45.916 --> 00:27:48.669
I saw it!
Why don't you believe me?

340
00:27:48.794 --> 00:27:50.254
It's not that I don't.

341
00:27:50.379 --> 00:27:53.382
There's a medical term for that.

342
00:27:53.966 --> 00:27:56.635
When excited and dopamine is.....
-No. no!

343
00:27:57.511 --> 00:27:59.346
I wasn't excited.
I saw very clearly.

344
00:27:59.471 --> 00:28:02.975
As soon as he came to. he
wanted meat which he couldn't eat.

345
00:28:03.100 --> 00:28:06.645
Hwang's hair turned white
when he grabbed him.

346
00:28:06.770 --> 00:28:08.230
And the tree.....

347
00:28:09.565 --> 00:28:11.442
What you said before.....
-Pardon?

348
00:28:11.567 --> 00:28:15.029
The donor had
an unusual body type?

349
00:28:15.154 --> 00:28:16.739
I mentioned that's a possibility.

350
00:28:16.864 --> 00:28:22.119
There must be more
organ transplant recipients. right?

351
00:28:58.656 --> 00:29:00.115
One more time!

352
00:29:16.340 --> 00:29:18.050
There must be pollen in the air.

353
00:29:19.343 --> 00:29:23.347
Wanna stop?
-Let's just keep going.

354
00:29:29.103 --> 00:29:30.562
It's the weekend.
Got no plans?

355
00:29:32.147 --> 00:29:34.817
No friends?
-I have no friends.

356
00:29:35.025 --> 00:29:38.028
Why? Because of your dad?

357
00:29:38.988 --> 00:29:41.365
Well. that too.

358
00:29:41.615 --> 00:29:44.410
It's because
I took a year off from being sick.

359
00:29:45.828 --> 00:29:47.288
I hear you.

360
00:29:48.163 --> 00:29:51.875
No friends because you're sick or
because they think you'll get sick.

361
00:29:53.127 --> 00:29:55.170
Superhumans are often lonely.

362
00:30:03.554 --> 00:30:05.014
Know what?
-No.

363
00:30:05.139 --> 00:30:07.141
I didn't ask yet.
-What is it?

364
00:30:09.810 --> 00:30:13.022
The villain is among
the same group of superhumans...

365
00:30:13.605 --> 00:30:16.025
...and he'll attack
the others. Why?

366
00:30:16.150 --> 00:30:17.651
So he can have
all the superpowers?

367
00:30:17.776 --> 00:30:21.488
Right! So we must find the villain
first! Before he steals our powers.

368
00:30:21.613 --> 00:30:23.324
Us?
-Yes. us.

369
00:30:24.742 --> 00:30:27.453
People with superpowers
become friends.

370
00:30:27.578 --> 00:30:29.705
Like the rich hang out
with the rich.

371
00:30:29.830 --> 00:30:32.207
Mister. Do this.
-Why?

372
00:30:32.333 --> 00:30:33.792
Just do it.

373
00:30:39.715 --> 00:30:42.509
If you get caught
by the villain. call me.

374
00:30:42.676 --> 00:30:44.678
I'll rescue our whole gang!

375
00:30:45.095 --> 00:30:46.555
Wan-seo!

376
00:30:51.143 --> 00:30:54.104
How do we know
who is the villain?

377
00:30:55.647 --> 00:30:57.107
We'll know.

378
00:30:57.358 --> 00:30:58.817
The way I see it....

379
00:31:01.070 --> 00:31:02.529
...that jerk is the villain.

380
00:31:03.155 --> 00:31:04.615
He's so selfish.

381
00:31:05.074 --> 00:31:06.533
He ate two chicken wings!

382
00:31:06.658 --> 00:31:09.536
Wan-seo! Ji-sung!

383
00:31:09.661 --> 00:31:11.372
I found it!

384
00:31:11.497 --> 00:31:13.999
I found my superpower!
Watch carefully.

385
00:31:14.500 --> 00:31:16.043
Watch me.

386
00:31:18.045 --> 00:31:19.546
Drum roll!

387
00:31:31.266 --> 00:31:33.602
What if I don't have a superpower?

388
00:31:33.727 --> 00:31:37.689
Why do I have just a circle
for a tattoo back here?

389
00:31:39.274 --> 00:31:41.360
Why do you want to have
a superpower?

390
00:31:42.236 --> 00:31:45.739
So I can use it to save
other people. like a hero.

391
00:31:46.115 --> 00:31:48.158
Not everyone with superpowers
become heroes.

392
00:31:48.867 --> 00:31:50.327
Why not?

393
00:31:51.787 --> 00:31:55.499
There's a cut line by
experience. activism....

394
00:31:55.749 --> 00:31:58.836
...number of people saved.
and degree of self-sacrifice.

395
00:31:58.961 --> 00:32:00.462
Not anyone can become heroes.

396
00:32:00.671 --> 00:32:03.549
Man. I don't like cut lines.

397
00:32:04.133 --> 00:32:06.301
Is he coming or not?

398
00:32:06.427 --> 00:32:08.095
Did he hack away
and find the others?

399
00:32:08.846 --> 00:32:10.305
Not sure. Ask him. yourself.

400
00:32:10.722 --> 00:32:12.307
You'll get a stomach ache
if you drink too much.

401
00:32:12.433 --> 00:32:16.228
Why is he always so late?
No manners.

402
00:32:16.353 --> 00:32:17.813
He could've texted.

403
00:32:22.276 --> 00:32:25.946
"SUPERPOWERS' CHAT GROUP
HELP ME!"

404
00:32:26.155 --> 00:32:27.990
"HWANG KI-DONG:
SAVE ME"

405
00:32:29.908 --> 00:32:31.994
Darn.
-I'll return the money.

406
00:32:32.119 --> 00:32:34.329
That's a given. you jerk!

407
00:32:34.455 --> 00:32:37.291
How can you get a jackpot
11 times from one spot?

408
00:32:37.458 --> 00:32:39.960
You broke it! Pay up!
Take off the shades!

409
00:32:40.210 --> 00:32:43.255
I don't think it's broken.

410
00:32:43.464 --> 00:32:45.174
I'll pay.
-Of course you will. stupid!

411
00:32:45.299 --> 00:32:48.302
I saw you snapping your fingers.
then winning the jackpot.

412
00:32:48.510 --> 00:32:50.095
Are you Pikachu.
making static electricity?

413
00:32:50.220 --> 00:32:51.889
I'm not Pikachu. sir.

414
00:32:53.849 --> 00:32:55.309
It's a superpower.

415
00:32:57.269 --> 00:32:58.979
Sure. Mr. Electro.

416
00:32:59.229 --> 00:33:01.648
I gotta report you to my boss!

417
00:33:01.815 --> 00:33:04.359
He'll teach you a lesson.

418
00:33:21.585 --> 00:33:23.629
You gotta push it.

419
00:33:24.630 --> 00:33:27.841
I told him he'd get a
stomach ache. but he drank 5!

420
00:33:27.966 --> 00:33:29.426
Where'd he go?

421
00:33:30.219 --> 00:33:32.554
Middle school kids can't come in.
It's not a PC room.

422
00:33:32.679 --> 00:33:34.681
I should be in high school.
I took a year off.

423
00:33:34.806 --> 00:33:37.142
High school or not.
you can't come in here.

424
00:33:37.267 --> 00:33:38.977
Yogurt drinks give me
a stomach ache.

425
00:33:39.645 --> 00:33:41.730
I didn't come to sell yogurt.

426
00:33:41.855 --> 00:33:43.315
I came to take that young man.

427
00:33:43.440 --> 00:33:46.318
He's not someone you can just take!

428
00:33:46.443 --> 00:33:48.111
He messed with our machine!

429
00:33:48.237 --> 00:33:50.364
Wait. How'd you reach them
without a cell phone?

430
00:33:50.489 --> 00:33:51.949
Excuse me.

431
00:33:52.074 --> 00:33:53.534
There's no toilet paper.

432
00:33:54.034 --> 00:33:55.494
There.

433
00:34:03.502 --> 00:34:04.962
It's so far.

434
00:34:06.880 --> 00:34:08.382
Is he a friend?
-No.

435
00:34:08.507 --> 00:34:10.968
Mister!
Let that man go.

436
00:34:11.093 --> 00:34:12.594
My dad is a Taekwondo master.

437
00:34:12.719 --> 00:34:14.471
My dad is a master ex-con!

438
00:34:14.596 --> 00:34:16.431
Didn't you hear anything
I said before?

439
00:34:16.557 --> 00:34:19.393
This man completely ruined
my business!

440
00:34:19.560 --> 00:34:22.980
I lost big time!
-He should pay up for that.

441
00:34:23.105 --> 00:34:24.565
We're not friends.

442
00:34:24.940 --> 00:34:26.441
He has no friends.

443
00:34:27.401 --> 00:34:29.111
He needs to be punished.

444
00:34:29.236 --> 00:34:31.071
He's hopeless.

445
00:34:31.405 --> 00:34:34.866
We're going for ribs.
If you learned your lesson. come.

446
00:34:34.992 --> 00:34:36.994
Or don't. I don't care.

447
00:34:38.495 --> 00:34:41.707
Can you just let him go. please?

448
00:34:41.832 --> 00:34:43.834
Wait!

449
00:34:45.794 --> 00:34:47.337
I'll give you drinks for free.

450
00:34:47.588 --> 00:34:51.842
Don't you people have ears?
I get diarrhea from those!

451
00:35:10.694 --> 00:35:12.654
Beef or pork ribs?

452
00:35:19.244 --> 00:35:20.704
They went in 10 minutes ago.

453
00:35:20.829 --> 00:35:22.289
All four are here?

454
00:35:25.876 --> 00:35:28.545
It took exactly 4 minutes
and 28 seconds. sir.

455
00:35:29.379 --> 00:35:30.839
Darn it!

456
00:35:43.310 --> 00:35:45.437
Oh! Wan-seo!

457
00:35:49.066 --> 00:35:50.525
Hop on!

458
00:35:57.491 --> 00:35:59.576
Call the boys!

459
00:36:20.055 --> 00:36:22.349
What's that?
-Pass them!

460
00:36:28.021 --> 00:36:29.648
Whoa! What the hell?

461
00:37:00.721 --> 00:37:02.180
What do we do?

462
00:37:02.723 --> 00:37:04.683
Step on it!

463
00:37:19.364 --> 00:37:21.199
Wan-seo!

464
00:38:02.741 --> 00:38:04.201
Now. swing!

465
00:38:37.067 --> 00:38:39.194
Stop or you're all dead meat!

466
00:38:42.155 --> 00:38:43.615
Think our truck is a joke?

467
00:38:43.740 --> 00:38:46.575
We'll race you down!

468
00:38:46.701 --> 00:38:49.663
Stop it. sneezer!

469
00:38:51.998 --> 00:38:53.750
Take your shades off!

470
00:39:25.574 --> 00:39:27.033
Stop!

471
00:39:34.958 --> 00:39:36.418
Table for 4. please.

472
00:39:40.046 --> 00:39:42.799
"RIB HOUSE"
-Thank you.

473
00:39:43.884 --> 00:39:45.927
All-you-can-eat is not bad!

474
00:39:46.051 --> 00:39:50.348
We almost died because of him.
but he doesn't even pay?

475
00:39:50.640 --> 00:39:52.684
You're acting like you paid. pal.

476
00:39:52.808 --> 00:39:54.351
I'm not your pal.
-I didn't mean it like that.

477
00:39:54.477 --> 00:39:57.063
Let's not fight among friends.

478
00:39:57.188 --> 00:39:58.648
What friends?

479
00:39:59.064 --> 00:40:01.192
This jerk!
Are we gonna keep going with him?

480
00:40:01.401 --> 00:40:04.195
If you can hack and find
the others. be my guest.

481
00:40:04.778 --> 00:40:06.948
It's not that I can't!
It's illegal.

482
00:40:07.115 --> 00:40:09.618
With such a strong sense
of the law....

483
00:40:09.743 --> 00:40:12.287
...why plagiarize
someone else's work?

484
00:40:13.872 --> 00:40:16.207
Did you hack my life?
-So what if I did?

485
00:40:16.458 --> 00:40:19.002
You act so righteous.
so I took a look.

486
00:40:19.210 --> 00:40:20.795
What writer?

487
00:40:20.921 --> 00:40:24.549
The only screenplay you sold
was stolen from a friend.

488
00:40:24.799 --> 00:40:26.384
That's why you got no friends.

489
00:40:40.482 --> 00:40:43.443
You're a big internet troll. huh?

490
00:40:43.568 --> 00:40:45.362
You got sued so many times!

491
00:40:45.486 --> 00:40:47.989
You give bad reviews
without even looking at things.

492
00:40:48.114 --> 00:40:49.615
And you're poor!

493
00:40:49.741 --> 00:40:52.035
Did you know that your stocks
are down 90%?

494
00:40:52.327 --> 00:40:53.786
You have $80 left.

495
00:40:55.747 --> 00:40:58.041
"F YOU"
-Work hard for your money....

496
00:40:58.166 --> 00:41:00.168
...righteously.
Aren't you sorry to your mom...

497
00:41:00.293 --> 00:41:02.169
...who works as a maid
to pay for your stocks?

498
00:41:02.295 --> 00:41:04.506
Mister! Don't!
-I'd kill myself if I were you.

499
00:41:04.631 --> 00:41:06.466
How can you say that!

500
00:41:07.175 --> 00:41:09.010
There are things
you shouldn't say!

501
00:41:09.886 --> 00:41:11.346
Suicide?

502
00:41:14.516 --> 00:41:16.267
Let's go. Don't mind him.

503
00:41:16.393 --> 00:41:18.561
For what! Move!

504
00:41:19.813 --> 00:41:21.980
Hey! Let go!
-Stop fighting!

505
00:41:22.107 --> 00:41:23.942
We promised to be friends!
-I felt sorry for you...

506
00:41:24.066 --> 00:41:26.861
...and played with you!
Think we're real friends now?

507
00:41:28.947 --> 00:41:30.407
Hey! Come here!

508
00:41:49.049 --> 00:41:51.052
What's wrong with you two!

509
00:41:51.469 --> 00:41:53.805
Let's not meet anymore. then!

510
00:42:18.079 --> 00:42:20.540
Why didn't you take my calls?
Where were you?

511
00:42:21.166 --> 00:42:22.625
What happened to this?

512
00:42:23.209 --> 00:42:25.586
Who were you with? Friends?

513
00:42:26.421 --> 00:42:27.881
I don't have friends.

514
00:42:28.381 --> 00:42:29.883
What did you do alone. then?

515
00:42:30.008 --> 00:42:31.634
Give me your friend's number.
-I don't have friends.

516
00:42:31.760 --> 00:42:33.385
I thought something
bad happened...

517
00:42:33.511 --> 00:42:35.180
...and checked
the police. hospital....

518
00:42:35.305 --> 00:42:36.806
...and even the morgue!

519
00:42:37.432 --> 00:42:39.434
I was so worried about you!

520
00:42:39.559 --> 00:42:42.062
You're not well. Don't go around
playing with friends!

521
00:42:42.187 --> 00:42:43.646
Darn it!

522
00:42:43.772 --> 00:42:45.898
I have no friends.

523
00:42:46.024 --> 00:42:47.734
Do you hear me?

524
00:42:48.902 --> 00:42:51.780
I have no one.
Everyone hates me!

525
00:42:51.905 --> 00:42:54.157
I'm a useless human being!

526
00:42:54.282 --> 00:42:57.660
Instead of living like this.
I should've just died then!

527
00:42:57.786 --> 00:43:00.789
Why would you die!
-Darn it!

528
00:43:01.247 --> 00:43:03.416
You're suffocating me. Dad!

529
00:43:04.000 --> 00:43:08.004
I feel like my heart will stop
because of you!

530
00:43:08.671 --> 00:43:10.131
I'm not a dog!

531
00:43:10.256 --> 00:43:12.926
Why put this leash on me?

532
00:43:14.260 --> 00:43:17.679
You're suffocating
me to death. Dad.

533
00:43:17.806 --> 00:43:19.432
I don't need you!

534
00:43:25.897 --> 00:43:29.109
Wan-seo.
Wan-seo. Wait!

535
00:43:29.234 --> 00:43:31.611
Don't run!
You'll fall!

536
00:43:58.304 --> 00:44:00.140
Have a drink before you go.

537
00:44:05.728 --> 00:44:07.647
Please stop bringing things.

538
00:44:10.066 --> 00:44:11.526
I'm sorry.

539
00:44:13.027 --> 00:44:16.948
I guess your kidney
transplant went well.

540
00:44:17.949 --> 00:44:19.450
You look much healthier.

541
00:44:21.326 --> 00:44:23.121
Your skin is glowing.

542
00:44:23.246 --> 00:44:26.166
You're more beautiful.

543
00:44:30.920 --> 00:44:34.424
You took 2 people's lives.
You should be healthier.

544
00:44:34.549 --> 00:44:36.009
Right?

545
00:44:39.095 --> 00:44:40.555
I'm so sorry.

546
00:44:41.181 --> 00:44:44.893
For the rest of my life.

547
00:44:45.018 --> 00:44:48.980
I'll do good deeds
on behalf of your husband...

548
00:44:49.980 --> 00:44:51.691
...and save many people.

549
00:44:51.816 --> 00:44:54.819
I just wish
you'd commit suicide again.

550
00:44:55.945 --> 00:44:58.448
Don't fail this time.
I hope you succeed.

551
00:44:58.573 --> 00:45:00.533
Don't start a fire to die....

552
00:45:00.658 --> 00:45:03.995
...then make an innocent person
like my husband die.

553
00:45:04.662 --> 00:45:06.414
I wish you'd die.

554
00:45:21.429 --> 00:45:22.889
Let's do this.

555
00:45:23.306 --> 00:45:24.766
What?

556
00:45:24.890 --> 00:45:27.644
Let's research this
and make new medicine.

557
00:45:27.769 --> 00:45:30.438
What do you mean?
-Are there 3 years left...

558
00:45:30.563 --> 00:45:33.231
...till retirement?
-3 and 4 months to be exact.

559
00:45:33.358 --> 00:45:35.068
After you retire....

560
00:45:35.235 --> 00:45:37.278
...want to change grandkids'
diapers...

561
00:45:37.402 --> 00:45:39.447
...or be the
pharmaceutical company VP?

562
00:45:40.030 --> 00:45:41.491
Pardon?

563
00:45:42.450 --> 00:45:44.077
It's about time...

564
00:45:44.786 --> 00:45:46.955
...a Korean wins the Nobel prize
for medicine. right?

565
00:45:47.121 --> 00:45:48.706
But how?

566
00:45:51.125 --> 00:45:52.877
I think there is a way.

567
00:45:53.002 --> 00:45:54.462
Why are you here?

568
00:45:54.671 --> 00:45:56.464
Are you set on not meeting them?

569
00:45:56.631 --> 00:45:58.091
That's what the lady said.

570
00:45:58.216 --> 00:46:00.093
But you wanted
to find the villain.

571
00:46:00.927 --> 00:46:03.221
The villain has been found.
No use looking.

572
00:46:04.012 --> 00:46:05.473
Come on.

573
00:46:05.597 --> 00:46:10.811
The snapping man is not a villain.
He's more like a minion.

574
00:46:11.020 --> 00:46:13.356
It's not him. I'm the villain.

575
00:46:15.191 --> 00:46:18.736
You know that if you're sick.
you don't care about things.

576
00:46:18.861 --> 00:46:20.947
Then people get on your nerves.

577
00:46:21.072 --> 00:46:24.033
And I hate myself for cursing
those that get on my nerves.

578
00:46:24.242 --> 00:46:27.078
It's a rule that losers
with nothing become the villain.

579
00:46:27.870 --> 00:46:29.914
But you have a superpower.

580
00:46:31.708 --> 00:46:33.167
What can I do with this?

581
00:46:34.043 --> 00:46:37.005
Why couldn't I get a cool.
useful one like that jerk?

582
00:46:37.171 --> 00:46:39.090
This is a joke. It's useless.

583
00:46:39.965 --> 00:46:43.093
What's wrong with you?
-This is why I'm living like this.

584
00:46:49.809 --> 00:46:51.686
I didn't plagiarize the script.

585
00:46:52.103 --> 00:46:54.522
We planned it together. but he
said he'd write something else.

586
00:46:54.647 --> 00:46:56.107
Forget it.

587
00:46:57.567 --> 00:46:59.027
Mister.

588
00:46:59.527 --> 00:47:01.779
Did you really play with me
because you felt sorry for me?

589
00:47:02.530 --> 00:47:03.989
I take that back.

590
00:47:05.450 --> 00:47:07.493
Go tell Seon-nyeo that I'm sorry.

591
00:47:08.118 --> 00:47:10.079
Go there and tell her yourself.

592
00:47:11.414 --> 00:47:14.751
Where?
-We found the liver recipient.

593
00:47:14.876 --> 00:47:17.962
Team chief 7. They're not
members of our congregation.

594
00:47:18.087 --> 00:47:22.550
If we cater to all their needs.
we can't finish before the revival.

595
00:47:22.716 --> 00:47:25.720
We went up 50 floors with no ropes
back in my days.

596
00:47:25.844 --> 00:47:28.931
Father God said safety
is most important. sir.

597
00:47:29.057 --> 00:47:32.393
That's right. He oversees
everything. What is there to worry?

598
00:47:33.061 --> 00:47:36.064
It's because they have no faith
that they're scared!

599
00:47:36.189 --> 00:47:38.274
Let's eat.
-Ward Chief.

600
00:47:38.398 --> 00:47:40.902
There are still 15 minutes left
till lunchtime.

601
00:47:41.986 --> 00:47:44.112
Let's eat. then work.
We're not robots.

602
00:47:44.238 --> 00:47:46.407
How can we finish this
in one day?

603
00:47:46.532 --> 00:47:47.992
Enjoy your lunch.

604
00:47:48.326 --> 00:47:51.537
To finish this today.
someone has to work.

605
00:47:51.662 --> 00:47:53.122
Jeez.

606
00:47:53.331 --> 00:47:55.208
Get me a cup of noodles?

607
00:47:55.458 --> 00:47:57.085
Sure.
-Thanks!

608
00:48:01.838 --> 00:48:04.175
"WHEN ARE YOU COMING. MISTER?"
-He's not coming.

609
00:48:04.300 --> 00:48:05.760
He saw it and didn't reply.

610
00:48:05.885 --> 00:48:08.094
So what if he doesn't?
He'll just take up oxygen.

611
00:48:08.221 --> 00:48:11.682
What a twisted guy
with a useless superpower.

612
00:48:12.642 --> 00:48:16.187
I'm sorry. but I'd better go.

613
00:48:16.312 --> 00:48:17.897
Go and meet him.

614
00:48:18.272 --> 00:48:21.526
Why? Don't you want to find
your superpower?

615
00:48:23.152 --> 00:48:27.740
I'm sorry. Wan-seo.
I have no right to be here.

616
00:48:27.865 --> 00:48:29.325
What do you mean?

617
00:48:30.076 --> 00:48:32.995
We promised to find your superpower
and become heroes together.

618
00:48:35.205 --> 00:48:38.376
You saw into my life too. right?

619
00:48:39.252 --> 00:48:40.837
You know I'm not qualified.

620
00:48:41.587 --> 00:48:44.340
Ah. I didn't look that
carefully.....

621
00:48:45.842 --> 00:48:48.511
Use your precious
powers for good.

622
00:48:48.636 --> 00:48:50.596
Thank you for everything.

623
00:48:53.641 --> 00:48:55.101
Then I quit too!

624
00:48:55.559 --> 00:48:57.019
This sucks.

625
00:48:58.771 --> 00:49:00.356
I struggle to survive too.

626
00:49:00.481 --> 00:49:02.858
What superhero?
Help others for what?

627
00:49:03.859 --> 00:49:06.446
Let's disband!
Our chatroom can go bust!

628
00:49:16.122 --> 00:49:18.749
They said it's nothing.
Don't worry.

629
00:49:18.875 --> 00:49:20.626
What are you doing?
-Can't you hear that?

630
00:49:20.751 --> 00:49:22.211
Get out! Hurry!

631
00:49:22.336 --> 00:49:25.298
The ward chief said it's nothing
and told us to stay.

632
00:49:25.423 --> 00:49:27.467
Think he'd be responsible
if you people die!

633
00:49:28.884 --> 00:49:30.344
Get out now!

634
00:49:30.595 --> 00:49:32.053
In two rows!

635
00:49:32.180 --> 00:49:33.639
Be careful!

636
00:49:45.485 --> 00:49:46.944
What was that?

637
00:49:51.032 --> 00:49:52.492
Hurry!

638
00:49:58.956 --> 00:50:02.292
Are we going the right way?
-I have no idea either!

639
00:50:07.882 --> 00:50:10.426
Seung-hoon!
Seung-hoon!

640
00:50:11.302 --> 00:50:13.471
Over here!

641
00:50:13.638 --> 00:50:16.098
Lee Seung-hoon!
-Help me. chief!

642
00:50:18.476 --> 00:50:20.478
Didn't we come here before?

643
00:50:21.354 --> 00:50:22.855
Help me!

644
00:50:22.980 --> 00:50:24.440
Seung-hoon!

645
00:50:25.149 --> 00:50:26.609
Put your safety hat on!

646
00:50:41.082 --> 00:50:42.792
Mister. move!

647
00:51:21.455 --> 00:51:22.915
Stay back.

648
00:51:23.457 --> 00:51:25.626
There's someone in there!
Ki-dong! Open the door!

649
00:51:25.751 --> 00:51:27.211
Mister. wait!
-Hurry!

650
00:51:27.336 --> 00:51:29.422
It's dangerous!
-Open it or not?

651
00:51:29.547 --> 00:51:31.007
Open it.

652
00:51:41.934 --> 00:51:43.393
I'm sorry about before.

653
00:51:52.945 --> 00:51:56.490
Are there any goggles here?
I can't see from all the smoke.

654
00:51:57.491 --> 00:51:58.951
Turn the music off!

655
00:52:00.620 --> 00:52:02.997
Ki-dong!
-I'm on it.

656
00:52:16.052 --> 00:52:18.679
Found him!
-I'll tell you the way. Go in!

657
00:52:18.804 --> 00:52:21.057
Who are you to tell me
to go in or not?

658
00:52:21.307 --> 00:52:23.142
I can give you the directions.

659
00:52:23.267 --> 00:52:25.478
Then why don't you just go in?

660
00:52:25.603 --> 00:52:27.188
Are you crazy! Don't fight!

661
00:52:27.313 --> 00:52:29.940
You said to open
the door. so I did.

662
00:52:30.066 --> 00:52:32.943
You asked for directions. so I did.
What more do you want?

663
00:52:33.069 --> 00:52:35.988
I'm saying. you don't get
to boss me around with orders.

664
00:52:36.113 --> 00:52:39.950
You're the one who's giving me
the orders! Don't you get it?

665
00:52:40.076 --> 00:52:42.620
You don't get to tell me
what to do!

666
00:52:42.745 --> 00:52:44.205
I don't take orders from you!

667
00:52:44.330 --> 00:52:46.207
You stupid!

668
00:52:46.332 --> 00:52:50.461
Stop fighting all the time!

669
00:52:50.586 --> 00:52:53.297
Get in there now!

670
00:52:57.051 --> 00:52:58.511
Give us the directions.

671
00:52:59.845 --> 00:53:01.514
What?

672
00:53:08.562 --> 00:53:11.357
Go left. A bit more.

673
00:53:12.024 --> 00:53:13.484
Not that way!

674
00:53:14.443 --> 00:53:16.112
Good.

675
00:53:16.362 --> 00:53:19.323
Go straight.
He's there!

676
00:53:31.085 --> 00:53:32.545
Seung-hoon!

677
00:53:32.837 --> 00:53:36.006
Is he okay?
-This way!

678
00:53:38.801 --> 00:53:40.261
Seung-hoon!

679
00:53:40.386 --> 00:53:42.346
Hey. pal! Wake up!

680
00:54:09.290 --> 00:54:10.750
Mister!

681
00:54:12.460 --> 00:54:15.296
Water.
-Water?

682
00:54:15.713 --> 00:54:19.425
Water! Hurry!
-Water!

683
00:54:19.592 --> 00:54:21.051
Hurry!

684
00:54:22.470 --> 00:54:24.054
Oh. no.

685
00:54:24.263 --> 00:54:26.223
Water! Where?

686
00:54:27.600 --> 00:54:29.977
Don't just stand there.
do something!

687
00:55:03.052 --> 00:55:04.512
What did you do?

688
00:55:16.649 --> 00:55:18.108
Which way?

689
00:55:20.736 --> 00:55:22.196
Stop!

690
00:55:24.448 --> 00:55:25.908
Where is Ki-dong?

691
00:55:29.203 --> 00:55:31.622
Where am I?
You said to get some water.

692
00:55:31.747 --> 00:55:33.457
If I say where.
can you find me?

693
00:55:34.959 --> 00:55:37.419
There's a water dispenser.
a superhero poster. and.....

694
00:55:55.437 --> 00:55:57.731
Go outside first.

695
00:55:59.275 --> 00:56:02.778
Water dispenser and poster?
I know where they are.

696
00:56:02.945 --> 00:56:05.447
Please take him outside.

697
00:56:06.365 --> 00:56:07.825
Follow me.

698
00:56:12.580 --> 00:56:14.039
Let's go.

699
00:57:00.878 --> 00:57:02.546
He's just 100 m away.

700
00:57:02.671 --> 00:57:05.549
Aren't there any gas masks
at a construction site like this?

701
00:57:06.175 --> 00:57:10.554
I'm sorry.
-I saw some tanks earlier.

702
00:57:10.679 --> 00:57:12.765
Aren't there any oxygen tanks?

703
00:57:12.890 --> 00:57:14.850
The oxygen tank has arrived!

704
00:57:26.570 --> 00:57:28.030
It's not that way.

705
00:58:55.409 --> 00:58:58.996
My name is Huh Heel-han.
I had a liver transplant.

706
00:58:59.121 --> 00:59:02.041
I can't always heal
pre-existing conditions.

707
00:59:02.166 --> 00:59:05.502
But I can heal fractures.
bruises. stiff shoulders....

708
00:59:05.627 --> 00:59:09.673
...and chronic fatigue
caused by accidents.

709
00:59:09.923 --> 00:59:12.301
Let me know if you need me.

710
00:59:13.677 --> 00:59:16.930
You drive part-time at nights too?
My dad. too.

711
00:59:17.056 --> 00:59:21.143
Back then. you healed people
and took the injuries on yourself.

712
00:59:21.268 --> 00:59:24.897
If I just drink some water.
I'm okay after a while.

713
00:59:25.022 --> 00:59:26.857
Wow.

714
00:59:27.066 --> 00:59:29.902
You're what they call a real hero!

715
00:59:30.110 --> 00:59:32.529
Right?
Applause!

716
00:59:34.656 --> 00:59:39.411
Ma'am.
I think you're the real hero.

717
00:59:39.536 --> 00:59:41.288
You saved my life.

718
00:59:41.413 --> 00:59:43.582
I sincerely thank you.

719
00:59:53.383 --> 00:59:54.843
What?
-Why?

720
00:59:54.968 --> 00:59:56.637
Why. what?
-I'm not sure why and what!

721
00:59:56.762 --> 00:59:58.514
Don't cry. lady!

722
00:59:58.639 --> 01:00:00.933
You swore like hell before.
Crying doesn't suit.

723
01:00:01.058 --> 01:00:02.726
You're scaring me!

724
01:00:04.561 --> 01:00:06.480
Actually. in the past....

725
01:00:06.605 --> 01:00:10.150
...I suffered from depression
and anger control disorder.

726
01:00:10.275 --> 01:00:14.738
After the transplant.
I got healthier and better.

727
01:00:14.863 --> 01:00:16.365
I thought swearing
was her superpower.

728
01:00:16.490 --> 01:00:17.950
Please!

729
01:00:18.408 --> 01:00:20.119
Forget all that.

730
01:00:20.244 --> 01:00:23.038
Why don't we name
ourselves as heroes?

731
01:00:23.163 --> 01:00:25.999
Why do that?
-In Hollywood movies....

732
01:00:26.125 --> 01:00:27.918
...superheroes all have names.

733
01:00:28.043 --> 01:00:30.045
Some sort of man or girl.

734
01:00:30.170 --> 01:00:34.341
I'm strong and fast like
a super cat with nine lives.

735
01:00:34.466 --> 01:00:37.261
How about Nine Girl?
-Are you sure?

736
01:00:38.303 --> 01:00:40.139
I like it in English.
Nine Girl.

737
01:00:40.848 --> 01:00:44.434
You're like an oxygen tank.
How about Tank Boy?

738
01:00:45.144 --> 01:00:46.603
What about you. ma'am?

739
01:00:46.728 --> 01:00:48.730
I'm a yogurt fresh manager.

740
01:00:48.856 --> 01:00:50.774
So I thought of Fresh Girl.

741
01:00:50.899 --> 01:00:52.776
Is it weird?

742
01:00:52.901 --> 01:00:57.823
Girl goes better than woman
with Fresh. doesn't it?

743
01:00:57.948 --> 01:01:00.742
Whatever you want.
I won't call you.

744
01:01:03.078 --> 01:01:06.206
Your name is Heel-han.
-Yes.

745
01:01:06.331 --> 01:01:09.459
How about Heal-hand?
Your hand heals.

746
01:01:11.295 --> 01:01:13.755
Since Ki-dong's name
means conductor.

747
01:01:13.881 --> 01:01:15.924
Bluetooth Man!
You control wi-fi and stuff.

748
01:01:16.049 --> 01:01:17.759
Right! That's good.

749
01:01:17.885 --> 01:01:19.344
Hey. Nine Girl.

750
01:01:19.678 --> 01:01:21.138
You suck at school. don't you?

751
01:01:21.263 --> 01:01:23.348
Dad just told me to be healthy.

752
01:01:23.599 --> 01:01:29.271
Wait.
I already have a name in mind.

753
01:01:29.521 --> 01:01:32.983
Since I heal
and recharge people's energy....

754
01:01:33.859 --> 01:01:35.319
...Battery Man.

755
01:01:36.612 --> 01:01:38.739
Since everyone else's names
are in English.....

756
01:01:38.906 --> 01:01:41.283
Right!
Nice! Battery Man!

757
01:01:41.867 --> 01:01:44.912
Now that we all have
new hero names and such...

758
01:01:45.037 --> 01:01:49.666
...Blues Man! Play some
music that suits the mood here!

759
01:01:52.669 --> 01:01:55.839
That's so cool!
Mister. this is cool. too.

760
01:01:55.964 --> 01:01:57.466
Watch this.

761
01:01:57.883 --> 01:01:59.343
Action!

762
01:02:06.308 --> 01:02:07.768
Wow!

763
01:02:11.104 --> 01:02:13.774
One more time!
-Stop it!

764
01:02:21.573 --> 01:02:25.118
"BARCELONA TAEKWONDO
BY 1992 OLYMPIC TEAM MEMBER"

765
01:02:26.370 --> 01:02:27.829
Where'd you go?

766
01:02:28.247 --> 01:02:29.706
I met some friends.

767
01:02:29.957 --> 01:02:32.501
You said you had no friends.
-I do now.

768
01:02:33.252 --> 01:02:36.296
Want some help?
-You have no strength.

769
01:02:38.632 --> 01:02:40.175
You'll get hurt. Move!

770
01:02:46.807 --> 01:02:49.434
See? Dad is still useful. huh?

771
01:02:49.559 --> 01:02:52.187
Not bad at all.
-Since I'm useful....

772
01:02:52.771 --> 01:02:55.691
...call me if you need my help.

773
01:02:55.857 --> 01:03:00.153
Dad.
-Even when you become a granny....

774
01:03:00.279 --> 01:03:02.739
...if you shout. "Dad!"

775
01:03:02.990 --> 01:03:06.702
I'll appear like a hero
and take care of everything.

776
01:03:09.037 --> 01:03:11.039
Catching a cold
is not good for the heart.

777
01:03:11.164 --> 01:03:13.417
Your doctor's appointment
is tomorrow. Go to bed.

778
01:03:15.210 --> 01:03:20.590
Our New God Hospital wishes
good health for our patients.

779
01:03:20.716 --> 01:03:24.219
All our medical staff is focused
on doing their best.

780
01:03:25.262 --> 01:03:27.139
I'm sorry.
Please take the next one.

781
01:03:28.140 --> 01:03:29.599
I'm sorry.

782
01:03:29.725 --> 01:03:31.435
"NEW GOD FOUNDATION"

783
01:03:32.436 --> 01:03:33.979
Let members on.

784
01:03:36.690 --> 01:03:38.150
What department are you in?

785
01:03:38.275 --> 01:03:39.735
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected!

786
01:03:39.860 --> 01:03:43.405
I'm Huh Heel-han.
stage equipment team chief 7. sir.

787
01:03:43.530 --> 01:03:45.490
It's an honor. sir!
-The recent explosion...

788
01:03:45.615 --> 01:03:47.242
...must've been a scare.
Were you hurt?

789
01:03:47.367 --> 01:03:49.453
I'm fine. sir. Thank you.

790
01:03:49.578 --> 01:03:51.955
You should thank your faith.

791
01:03:53.457 --> 01:03:56.043
Yes. sir.
I'll strive for more faith.

792
01:03:58.587 --> 01:04:01.798
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected.

793
01:04:22.986 --> 01:04:25.447
You have a tattoo?
-I was lucky...

794
01:04:25.572 --> 01:04:27.532
...to receive
a transplant recently. and.....

795
01:04:27.657 --> 01:04:29.117
What did you receive?

796
01:04:30.160 --> 01:04:32.204
The liver. sir.
-Did anything change...

797
01:04:32.329 --> 01:04:33.789
...after the surgery?

798
01:04:34.539 --> 01:04:36.291
I got much healthier.
less tired. and.....

799
01:04:36.416 --> 01:04:38.835
Not that.
Anything unusual?

800
01:04:41.004 --> 01:04:42.756
Well.....

801
01:04:42.881 --> 01:04:48.220
I'm not sure. but people say
I look younger.

802
01:05:00.023 --> 01:05:02.317
The liver is best
to being younger.

803
01:05:02.442 --> 01:05:03.902
What is your name again?

804
01:05:04.319 --> 01:05:06.238
Huh Heel-han. sir.

805
01:05:06.530 --> 01:05:08.657
Huh Heel-han. team chief 7.

806
01:05:09.658 --> 01:05:11.201
Take good care of yourself.

807
01:05:11.910 --> 01:05:13.412
I'll see you again.

808
01:05:16.790 --> 01:05:18.708
"ALL ABOUT NURSING"
-Is someone preparing...

809
01:05:18.834 --> 01:05:22.629
...to become a nurse?
-No. I'm just reading it for fun.

810
01:05:22.838 --> 01:05:25.298
That's cool.

811
01:05:25.549 --> 01:05:28.593
I'm sorry.
The location has been changed.

812
01:05:28.927 --> 01:05:30.679
Why meet here?

813
01:05:31.012 --> 01:05:33.682
Should I turn back?
-So sorry.

814
01:05:33.932 --> 01:05:35.392
Let's see.....

815
01:05:36.017 --> 01:05:37.936
Where is New God Pharmaceuticals?

816
01:05:38.061 --> 01:05:43.442
I work right beside that company.
I know the way well.

817
01:05:43.692 --> 01:05:47.863
That's great.
Please drive there safely.

818
01:05:47.988 --> 01:05:50.782
Of course.
-I had some gum here.

819
01:05:50.907 --> 01:05:52.367
Gum?

820
01:05:53.535 --> 01:05:55.454
Why aren't you starting?

821
01:05:56.455 --> 01:05:58.832
Ah. well.....

822
01:05:59.082 --> 01:06:01.376
The biopsy needs to be done first.

823
01:06:01.501 --> 01:06:04.421
The anesthesia won't work
even past lethal levels.

824
01:06:05.172 --> 01:06:06.673
Arch priest?

825
01:06:07.549 --> 01:06:11.428
What a relief. I'm team
chief 7. Huh Heel-han.

826
01:06:11.845 --> 01:06:15.098
Arch priest?
Where am I? I gotta go home.

827
01:06:15.223 --> 01:06:16.683
Wait!

828
01:06:17.058 --> 01:06:21.313
I summarized all the core points
to the nursing exam book.

829
01:06:21.480 --> 01:06:24.232
Do you know where it is?
-Forget anesthesia. Just cut him.

830
01:06:26.818 --> 01:06:29.738
Arch priest! Help!

831
01:06:29.863 --> 01:06:31.865
Arch priest!
Arch priest!

832
01:06:31.990 --> 01:06:33.450
Shut up!

833
01:06:34.493 --> 01:06:35.994
Arch priest.....

834
01:06:37.120 --> 01:06:39.873
Just make him faint or something.

835
01:06:40.874 --> 01:06:42.626
What's keeping you?
-Pardon?

836
01:06:42.751 --> 01:06:45.587
Waiting for someone?
-Me. of course.

837
01:06:47.464 --> 01:06:50.342
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected.

838
01:06:53.136 --> 01:06:55.680
What you planned is amusing.

839
01:06:59.434 --> 01:07:01.853
We meet again.
Huh Heel-han. team chief 7.

840
01:07:01.978 --> 01:07:04.814
It's okay.
Who did this to you?

841
01:07:06.233 --> 01:07:08.318
Dr. Song!
-Yes. Father God.

842
01:07:08.568 --> 01:07:11.863
If you leave a bit.
the liver can grow back. right?

843
01:07:11.988 --> 01:07:13.448
Yes. sir.

844
01:07:14.866 --> 01:07:17.244
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected.

845
01:07:18.161 --> 01:07:19.913
Become a true sacrifice...

846
01:07:20.038 --> 01:07:22.040
...and live eternally in me.

847
01:07:42.936 --> 01:07:44.479
Dr. Kim. Tie him!

848
01:08:04.666 --> 01:08:06.668
I'm sorry!
-I guess it doesn't work...

849
01:08:06.793 --> 01:08:08.253
...on the same kind.

850
01:08:09.921 --> 01:08:11.381
Let's do the transplant.

851
01:08:31.985 --> 01:08:34.529
Chief Cho.
-Yes. boss.

852
01:08:36.531 --> 01:08:37.991
Let's beat him to it.

853
01:08:38.950 --> 01:08:40.910
Capture all of them.

854
01:08:42.829 --> 01:08:46.875
Thank you! Slow down!

855
01:09:00.096 --> 01:09:01.556
Hey. lady! Over here!

856
01:09:01.681 --> 01:09:03.141
Coming!

857
01:09:04.976 --> 01:09:07.479
Thank you very much.

858
01:09:21.451 --> 01:09:24.621
Got anything good?
-Yes. of course I do!

859
01:09:24.788 --> 01:09:27.082
I have prebiotics and.....

860
01:09:39.969 --> 01:09:43.682
Sweetie!
What's wrong? What happened?

861
01:09:43.807 --> 01:09:46.893
Are you okay?
-Get the girl.

862
01:09:48.353 --> 01:09:51.106
All this for one little girl?
-Who are you?

863
01:09:51.356 --> 01:09:52.857
Let's go.
Where?

864
01:09:52.982 --> 01:09:56.986
It won't take long.
-Sweetie! Go over there!

865
01:09:57.529 --> 01:09:59.072
Stay back!

866
01:10:15.714 --> 01:10:18.091
Ow. my back!
I didn't get to stretch!

867
01:10:20.927 --> 01:10:22.679
Time out!

868
01:10:35.692 --> 01:10:37.152
Go back.

869
01:11:03.136 --> 01:11:05.430
You got this!
-Go all at once! Hurry!

870
01:11:18.443 --> 01:11:20.278
Fight back!

871
01:11:40.465 --> 01:11:42.550
Ever seen a 540-degree kick?

872
01:11:48.681 --> 01:11:51.434
Hi. Mom. I finished the kimchi.
I'll bring the container now.

873
01:11:56.064 --> 01:11:57.649
I told you to yell. "Dad!"
when you're in trouble.

874
01:11:57.774 --> 01:11:59.359
Get the water.
-Water?

875
01:11:59.483 --> 01:12:00.944
It's in the bag.

876
01:12:20.630 --> 01:12:22.090
Help!

877
01:12:33.393 --> 01:12:37.438
As I said before.
you got the wrong person.

878
01:12:37.564 --> 01:12:39.232
If you let me out.....

879
01:12:48.199 --> 01:12:50.201
Let me go.
-Did my dad...

880
01:12:50.326 --> 01:12:51.786
...promise you a position?

881
01:12:51.911 --> 01:12:57.083
I don't need a position.
A few Nobel prizes will do.

882
01:13:00.461 --> 01:13:03.214
Look.
You got in the wrong line.

883
01:13:04.799 --> 01:13:06.259
The old man can keep trying.

884
01:13:06.926 --> 01:13:09.261
But who do you think
will live longer?

885
01:13:10.680 --> 01:13:12.389
See for yourself.

886
01:13:22.650 --> 01:13:24.110
Who are you?

887
01:13:24.235 --> 01:13:25.695
What took you so long?

888
01:13:34.286 --> 01:13:35.872
Who the hell are you?

889
01:13:35.997 --> 01:13:38.791
Are you drunk?
Can't you recognize your father?

890
01:13:40.001 --> 01:13:44.172
I told you I was handsome
when I was young. didn't I?

891
01:13:48.468 --> 01:13:49.926
Why you.....

892
01:16:36.010 --> 01:16:38.845
Welcome! Follow me. please!

893
01:16:40.264 --> 01:16:42.725
This way. please.

894
01:16:42.934 --> 01:16:46.687
Pastor!
-Please watch the stairs. This way!

895
01:16:47.522 --> 01:16:49.148
This way. please.

896
01:16:49.272 --> 01:16:53.069
New members. right this way!

897
01:17:04.497 --> 01:17:07.208
Where are they?
My fellow recipients.

898
01:17:07.625 --> 01:17:11.253
I don't know.
-I need the others to become a god.

899
01:17:11.462 --> 01:17:12.922
Have you no fear?

900
01:17:13.422 --> 01:17:16.424
If there is a god.
you'll be punished for this.

901
01:17:19.553 --> 01:17:22.014
Are you going to church now?
-Dad!

902
01:17:22.140 --> 01:17:25.434
I'm trying to be a god
because I know I won't be forgiven.

903
01:17:35.235 --> 01:17:37.864
She's smart to hide them
right under my nose.

904
01:17:40.241 --> 01:17:41.951
Long time no see. Chief Cho.

905
01:17:42.076 --> 01:17:44.745
Who are you?
-You know who I am.

906
01:17:44.871 --> 01:17:46.330
No. I don't.

907
01:17:48.249 --> 01:17:51.169
Be gentle. Boss said
to escort him respectfully.

908
01:18:27.496 --> 01:18:28.956
Shit.

909
01:18:33.753 --> 01:18:37.256
Cramp! Cramp!

910
01:18:39.467 --> 01:18:42.220
"Where are you!"

911
01:19:07.495 --> 01:19:09.705
What? Did you open it?

912
01:19:10.248 --> 01:19:12.165
We came together. sir.

913
01:19:12.959 --> 01:19:15.127
Untie me now!

914
01:19:16.462 --> 01:19:18.089
Park Ji-sung! Ji-sung!

915
01:19:19.757 --> 01:19:24.929
That jerk!
Lady! Help! Lady! Lady!

916
01:19:26.013 --> 01:19:27.473
Darn it!

917
01:19:34.397 --> 01:19:35.856
"KI-DONG: HELP!"

918
01:19:36.357 --> 01:19:37.817
"WE'RE HELD HOSTAGE!"

919
01:19:40.569 --> 01:19:42.029
"ADDRESS?"

920
01:19:42.947 --> 01:19:44.407
"GO TO MAP"

921
01:19:56.669 --> 01:19:59.714
Not the eyes! No!

922
01:19:59.839 --> 01:20:01.424
Not my eyes!

923
01:20:03.258 --> 01:20:06.095
No! Take my willy instead!

924
01:20:06.512 --> 01:20:08.347
What a crybaby.

925
01:20:11.851 --> 01:20:13.311
Cornea transplant
is a breeze. right?

926
01:20:13.436 --> 01:20:15.980
Yes. sir.
-No way!

927
01:20:16.105 --> 01:20:17.565
Not my eyes!

928
01:20:17.690 --> 01:20:19.442
Why not do all the transplants
at once?

929
01:20:20.359 --> 01:20:22.194
I'm filthy rich!
-We need one more person.

930
01:20:22.320 --> 01:20:26.365
I'll give you money!
-It's better to do it one by one.

931
01:20:26.490 --> 01:20:28.909
How much will it take. jerk!

932
01:20:29.535 --> 01:20:34.040
Anesthesia will work on him. right?
Huh yelled way too much.

933
01:20:34.915 --> 01:20:38.752
I guess it hurt a lot.

934
01:20:53.225 --> 01:20:54.685
No.
-On what?

935
01:20:54.810 --> 01:20:56.270
Whatever it is.
-But I have to go.

936
01:20:56.394 --> 01:20:58.689
No! No way! You can't go!

937
01:21:00.900 --> 01:21:02.818
Think I didn't know
you went around in secret?

938
01:21:05.488 --> 01:21:08.449
When did you find out?
-Just by smelling...

939
01:21:08.574 --> 01:21:10.201
...our kid's fart....

940
01:21:10.326 --> 01:21:12.745
...we. parents.
know there's something wrong.

941
01:21:12.870 --> 01:21:15.706
3 years in the hospital.
you couldn't meet any friends.

942
01:21:17.083 --> 01:21:19.168
Since you got better.
you met new ones.

943
01:21:20.169 --> 01:21:22.338
But why do those friends
have to be...

944
01:21:24.757 --> 01:21:26.217
...school bullies!

945
01:21:29.470 --> 01:21:31.472
I buy you new shoes....

946
01:21:31.597 --> 01:21:34.266
...but you come back
with worn out. useless ones.

947
01:21:35.810 --> 01:21:38.896
My poor. weak baby girl!

948
01:21:39.021 --> 01:21:42.191
So this is why you wanted
to learn Taekwondo?

949
01:21:42.315 --> 01:21:45.111
To avoid getting hit?
To avoid bullies?

950
01:21:45.236 --> 01:21:46.987
Since the bullies torture you.
you wanted to learn.

951
01:21:47.113 --> 01:21:50.950
Dad.
-That's why.....

952
01:21:51.075 --> 01:21:52.910
Actually.....
-What if you get sick again?

953
01:21:53.035 --> 01:21:55.079
My friends are held hostage
by bullies now.

954
01:21:55.204 --> 01:21:57.706
I'm worried to death.

955
01:21:57.832 --> 01:22:01.419
We're like family.
I gotta go and rescue them.

956
01:22:01.544 --> 01:22:04.338
No! You can't!

957
01:22:08.050 --> 01:22:10.386
Hide behind me.
Those jerks!

958
01:22:10.510 --> 01:22:12.263
You saw me with the black suits.

959
01:22:12.388 --> 01:22:14.140
Age is just a number.

960
01:22:14.557 --> 01:22:16.016
Let's change the song.

961
01:22:16.142 --> 01:22:18.477
This song still makes
my blood boil.

962
01:22:18.602 --> 01:22:21.980
I won gold in Barcelona
after listening to this.

963
01:22:22.106 --> 01:22:23.566
What's my nickname?

964
01:22:23.691 --> 01:22:25.359
Taekwon V!
-Taekwon V!

965
01:22:25.484 --> 01:22:28.320
I won with my kick of justice!

966
01:22:38.372 --> 01:22:39.832
What?

967
01:22:40.040 --> 01:22:42.460
Come on. Snap to it!

968
01:22:42.585 --> 01:22:44.044
Where are we?

969
01:22:45.588 --> 01:22:47.047
We've been abducted.

970
01:22:48.257 --> 01:22:50.926
Let's get out.

971
01:22:56.223 --> 01:23:00.019
Where is the bathroom?
-Not that way.

972
01:23:04.815 --> 01:23:06.275
Are you okay. sir?

973
01:23:06.400 --> 01:23:08.110
This is so fun and amazing.

974
01:23:08.986 --> 01:23:11.780
Ever seen wi-fi signals?

975
01:23:13.991 --> 01:23:17.745
The focus goes in and out
with just one eye done.

976
01:23:17.912 --> 01:23:21.707
I'm sorry. sir. He suddenly
woke up and attacked.

977
01:23:21.916 --> 01:23:25.377
It bothers me that
he still has a cornea.

978
01:23:25.501 --> 01:23:28.630
He can see and do all this too.

979
01:23:30.049 --> 01:23:32.593
It was damaged during extraction.

980
01:23:32.718 --> 01:23:35.012
No treatment can help
recover it. sir.

981
01:23:48.901 --> 01:23:50.736
Who is it?
-It's me.

982
01:23:51.237 --> 01:23:53.864
Battery Man.
-Mister! Please heal me.

983
01:23:53.989 --> 01:23:56.075
You can heal people!

984
01:23:56.325 --> 01:23:58.077
My battery is dead.

985
01:23:58.202 --> 01:24:01.413
If you drink water.
you can recover. Please help me.

986
01:24:01.539 --> 01:24:03.541
I brought you water last time!

987
01:24:03.916 --> 01:24:08.170
I'm so scared.

988
01:24:09.755 --> 01:24:15.469
How can I go blind twice in life!

989
01:24:28.064 --> 01:24:30.109
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected.

990
01:24:31.485 --> 01:24:35.239
Welcome all members
and new followers who have come!

991
01:24:35.531 --> 01:24:38.701
Now. remember his promise!

992
01:24:38.826 --> 01:24:41.287
With a new. everlasting body....

993
01:24:41.412 --> 01:24:43.372
...he will return to save us
from the fires of hell...

994
01:24:43.497 --> 01:24:46.000
...and punish the unbelievers.
He has resurrected!

995
01:24:46.125 --> 01:24:47.585
The king of kings
and lord of lords!

996
01:24:47.710 --> 01:24:49.211
Let's welcome our Father God.
Seo Young-chun!

997
01:24:49.336 --> 01:24:51.422
Hands up high!
-Let's shout together.

998
01:24:51.547 --> 01:24:53.089
Father God!
-Father God!

999
01:24:53.215 --> 01:24:54.675
Father!

1000
01:25:12.610 --> 01:25:14.194
Who's that?
-I don't know.

1001
01:25:30.127 --> 01:25:31.837
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected.

1002
01:25:31.962 --> 01:25:34.214
Forever immortal.
transcendent body.

1003
01:25:35.007 --> 01:25:39.887
On the day I promised.
I shall return in a youthful body.

1004
01:25:40.011 --> 01:25:44.391
Those who believe and follow me
will be my people!

1005
01:26:14.504 --> 01:26:17.132
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected!

1006
01:26:17.257 --> 01:26:19.634
All powerful
to cut through rock!

1007
01:26:20.260 --> 01:26:24.889
On the day I promised. I'll break
the rock and show my power.

1008
01:26:25.140 --> 01:26:26.642
Those who believe and follow me...

1009
01:26:26.767 --> 01:26:29.770
...will be my people!

1010
01:26:49.707 --> 01:26:51.166
What?

1011
01:26:54.085 --> 01:26:56.380
What's happening?

1012
01:27:36.670 --> 01:27:39.590
Thank you!
Thank you. sir!

1013
01:27:39.882 --> 01:27:41.341
Father God!

1014
01:28:18.796 --> 01:28:20.255
Father!

1015
01:28:20.380 --> 01:28:22.925
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected.

1016
01:28:23.799 --> 01:28:25.885
Healer of all creation!

1017
01:28:27.471 --> 01:28:31.934
I shall heal the sick
and revive the dead!

1018
01:28:33.100 --> 01:28:34.561
I can walk!

1019
01:28:38.397 --> 01:28:39.858
Father God! Thank you!

1020
01:28:39.983 --> 01:28:42.986
All hail. the New God!

1021
01:28:43.862 --> 01:28:45.322
All who believe in me!

1022
01:28:47.574 --> 01:28:49.409
You will be my people!

1023
01:28:52.995 --> 01:28:56.208
Father God!

1024
01:29:03.924 --> 01:29:05.384
God has resurrected!

1025
01:29:15.978 --> 01:29:17.813
Why are there so many entrances?

1026
01:29:18.856 --> 01:29:20.315
Is a celebrity here?

1027
01:29:38.791 --> 01:29:40.252
Jesus Christ!

1028
01:29:43.714 --> 01:29:45.173
Scared me.

1029
01:29:46.090 --> 01:29:47.551
Don't run!

1030
01:29:50.387 --> 01:29:51.847
Wow!

1031
01:29:57.643 --> 01:30:00.147
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected.

1032
01:30:00.397 --> 01:30:03.066
I shall return as a perfect god!

1033
01:30:03.358 --> 01:30:05.569
Praise me with all your might!

1034
01:30:30.260 --> 01:30:32.638
So. you're Wan-seo?
-Who are you?

1035
01:30:32.763 --> 01:30:34.222
Such a pretty girl.

1036
01:30:35.849 --> 01:30:39.937
Mr. Park Jong-min!
The hero of Barcelona!

1037
01:30:40.187 --> 01:30:43.106
I was quite the fighter
back in the day too.

1038
01:30:43.357 --> 01:30:44.816
Glad to meet you.

1039
01:30:51.239 --> 01:30:54.034
Darn.

1040
01:31:16.515 --> 01:31:17.975
That hurt!

1041
01:31:18.725 --> 01:31:21.228
Didn't you teach your daughter
some manners?

1042
01:31:21.353 --> 01:31:23.772
How dare she kick an elder?
-Sorry.

1043
01:31:25.649 --> 01:31:28.359
But why are you yelling at me?

1044
01:31:28.485 --> 01:31:31.029
I get it!
You're the bully. aren't you!

1045
01:31:31.905 --> 01:31:33.907
How dare you yell at an elder!

1046
01:31:34.532 --> 01:31:36.617
Disrespectful jerk!
Don't you have a father?

1047
01:31:36.743 --> 01:31:38.245
Of course. he passed on.

1048
01:31:38.370 --> 01:31:40.706
He was born in 1905.

1049
01:31:40.914 --> 01:31:42.582
Did you take my friends?

1050
01:31:42.708 --> 01:31:44.209
Jeez.

1051
01:31:44.584 --> 01:31:47.086
Actually. my daughter did.
-Daughter?

1052
01:31:47.254 --> 01:31:49.798
She changed religions
and is up to no good.

1053
01:31:50.882 --> 01:31:54.845
Enough with the introductions.
Let's get to the point.

1054
01:31:56.888 --> 01:31:58.348
Wan-seo.

1055
01:31:59.016 --> 01:32:02.102
I need your heart.
-Are you out of your mind!

1056
01:32:04.770 --> 01:32:06.398
Nine Girl!

1057
01:32:18.994 --> 01:32:21.121
Nine Girl! Are you okay?

1058
01:32:21.246 --> 01:32:23.165
I was about to come for you.

1059
01:32:23.290 --> 01:32:25.042
Welcome.
But how'd you get out?

1060
01:32:25.167 --> 01:32:28.045
Are you Wan-seo's father?
How do you do?

1061
01:32:28.170 --> 01:32:30.964
I'll give you time
to say your final farewells.

1062
01:32:31.089 --> 01:32:34.384
I'm called Fresh Girl.

1063
01:32:34.509 --> 01:32:37.054
This is Tank Boy.
-Don't.....

1064
01:32:37.178 --> 01:32:41.141
You must be so proud of her.
-Yes. I am.

1065
01:32:41.265 --> 01:32:45.145
But I'm worried that
she's childish and so weak.

1066
01:32:45.270 --> 01:32:47.689
Do you have kids. Tank Girl?

1067
01:32:47.814 --> 01:32:49.274
It's Fresh Girl.
-Sorry.

1068
01:32:49.399 --> 01:32:50.859
Ms. Kim Seon-nyeo!

1069
01:32:51.902 --> 01:32:53.695
Let me talk. will you?
-Who are you?

1070
01:32:53.819 --> 01:32:56.782
I'm Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected.....

1071
01:32:56.906 --> 01:33:00.368
Mister! That bro is the
villain. He has a tattoo.

1072
01:33:01.995 --> 01:33:04.288
Why is he a bro and I'm a Mister?

1073
01:33:04.414 --> 01:33:05.874
He's cute.

1074
01:33:07.876 --> 01:33:11.254
Well. you look like a type
who needs to be cared for.

1075
01:33:13.423 --> 01:33:16.301
How dare you interrupt
when I'm talking?

1076
01:33:16.426 --> 01:33:17.886
What?

1077
01:33:18.345 --> 01:33:20.722
Where is Ki-dong and Mr. Huh?

1078
01:33:23.475 --> 01:33:24.935
I ate them.

1079
01:33:25.435 --> 01:33:27.646
You jerk!
-Wait.

1080
01:33:42.160 --> 01:33:43.620
Not dead. right?

1081
01:34:54.191 --> 01:34:55.650
Oh. no!

1082
01:34:58.111 --> 01:35:00.906
Are you okay?
-Hey! Let go!

1083
01:35:01.030 --> 01:35:03.491
Hurry!
He's coming!

1084
01:35:03.742 --> 01:35:05.200
Park Ji-sung.

1085
01:35:05.368 --> 01:35:07.454
Lung recipient. Your job is.....

1086
01:35:07.579 --> 01:35:10.290
Moonlight big chew!

1087
01:35:17.547 --> 01:35:19.007
Is he dead?

1088
01:35:19.591 --> 01:35:21.134
What did you just say?

1089
01:35:22.552 --> 01:35:25.054
It's good manners to tell
the name of your lethal move.

1090
01:35:27.224 --> 01:35:30.060
Gross! You spit all over me.

1091
01:35:30.769 --> 01:35:33.395
Moonlight what?

1092
01:35:36.149 --> 01:35:37.609
What does that mean?

1093
01:35:48.036 --> 01:35:49.496
Oh. my!

1094
01:35:54.376 --> 01:35:55.835
Get back.

1095
01:35:56.628 --> 01:35:58.755
Ginseng big.....
-Blow!

1096
01:36:06.679 --> 01:36:10.725
Let's see.
Kim Seon-nyeo's tattoo is here.

1097
01:36:29.160 --> 01:36:31.329
There was an easier way!

1098
01:36:31.997 --> 01:36:36.293
With you on my side.
I didn't have to do all that work.

1099
01:36:36.418 --> 01:36:37.877
Help me.

1100
01:36:38.001 --> 01:36:40.380
I know it's easy for you
to hand over their powers to me.

1101
01:36:40.505 --> 01:36:41.965
No! Get away from me!

1102
01:36:42.090 --> 01:36:45.385
Just pass over
their powers to me.

1103
01:36:45.677 --> 01:36:47.470
No need for blood shed.

1104
01:36:47.595 --> 01:36:50.765
Want to own a yogurt company?

1105
01:37:00.859 --> 01:37:02.736
Give me my eyeball!

1106
01:37:04.779 --> 01:37:07.073
Darn Dr. Song.
I knew the cornea.....

1107
01:37:34.851 --> 01:37:37.228
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected.

1108
01:37:37.354 --> 01:37:41.191
Be a true sacrifice
and live forever in me.

1109
01:37:41.316 --> 01:37:43.151
Why are you doing this?

1110
01:37:43.818 --> 01:37:47.821
There are two things
that I wanted my whole life.

1111
01:37:48.740 --> 01:37:50.283
One is youth.

1112
01:37:52.702 --> 01:37:55.622
You should ask what's the other one
for me to continue!

1113
01:37:58.083 --> 01:38:00.752
The other is.....
-You wanted to be god. right?

1114
01:38:01.086 --> 01:38:02.879
The world needs to see a god?

1115
01:38:03.421 --> 01:38:04.881
You'll become one to save people?

1116
01:38:05.006 --> 01:38:07.175
That's your nonsense story.
isn't it?

1117
01:38:07.300 --> 01:38:09.469
You must've read up on cults.

1118
01:38:09.594 --> 01:38:12.263
But lines like that
will get trolled!

1119
01:38:12.389 --> 01:38:14.682
You have a knack
for making people angry.

1120
01:38:14.808 --> 01:38:17.143
He's a famous online troll.
-Shut up.

1121
01:38:17.268 --> 01:38:20.187
Father God!
-What is it. Heel-han?

1122
01:38:21.271 --> 01:38:22.732
Was it all fake?

1123
01:38:23.525 --> 01:38:25.944
Was everything you showed us fake?

1124
01:38:26.485 --> 01:38:27.987
I left my entire family...

1125
01:38:28.196 --> 01:38:30.824
...and offered everything
that I made working day and night!

1126
01:38:31.449 --> 01:38:32.992
I offered up my life!

1127
01:38:34.494 --> 01:38:36.996
I was fooled
and did it all for nothing?

1128
01:38:37.414 --> 01:38:38.873
Yes.

1129
01:38:39.040 --> 01:38:43.920
So if you want to see a real god.
dedicate your lowly bodies to me.

1130
01:38:46.381 --> 01:38:49.217
Give me my eye. you jerk!

1131
01:38:53.221 --> 01:38:56.433
Go away! Why'd you throw that?

1132
01:38:57.559 --> 01:38:59.018
He's coming!

1133
01:39:15.910 --> 01:39:17.370
She's floating!

1134
01:40:02.372 --> 01:40:04.042
Should I die my hair?

1135
01:40:29.441 --> 01:40:32.653
We will offer up everything
to our Father God!

1136
01:40:32.779 --> 01:40:35.949
Our bodies. families.
assets. and everything!

1137
01:40:36.115 --> 01:40:38.034
Then we will be saved!

1138
01:41:05.186 --> 01:41:08.021
"FUTURE SCIENCE EXHIBITION"

1139
01:41:10.692 --> 01:41:12.192
"OFF LIMITS. WATCH ONLY"

1140
01:41:27.166 --> 01:41:29.544
Father God! Father God!

1141
01:41:31.129 --> 01:41:33.381
We pledge to offer our lives!

1142
01:41:33.506 --> 01:41:35.842
This can't be!
-What's wrong?

1143
01:41:35.967 --> 01:41:39.053
If this goes off. the tanks
will catch fire and kill everyone!

1144
01:42:03.870 --> 01:42:05.788
Wait! Hold on!

1145
01:42:05.913 --> 01:42:07.415
Let me catch my breath.

1146
01:42:09.334 --> 01:42:10.793
Winnie the.....

1147
01:42:17.258 --> 01:42:19.302
Will you kill everyone up there?

1148
01:42:20.303 --> 01:42:22.305
Will you kill all your followers?

1149
01:42:22.430 --> 01:42:24.432
I can always make new followers.

1150
01:42:25.223 --> 01:42:27.350
I'm the god of death.

1151
01:42:36.693 --> 01:42:38.154
You did this. not me.

1152
01:43:00.385 --> 01:43:02.803
Eternal Young-chun.
New God resurrected.

1153
01:43:02.970 --> 01:43:06.057
Be a part of me
and enjoy eternal life.

1154
01:43:08.351 --> 01:43:10.603
Kim Seon-nyeo! Hand them over!

1155
01:43:13.940 --> 01:43:15.942
Or you're all dead.

1156
01:43:19.570 --> 01:43:21.030
Open your eyes!

1157
01:43:22.572 --> 01:43:24.534
Park Wan-seo!

1158
01:43:32.875 --> 01:43:35.461
Die. you jerk!

1159
01:43:42.885 --> 01:43:44.345
No!

1160
01:43:49.392 --> 01:43:50.852
No!

1161
01:46:16.080 --> 01:46:17.540
Nine Girl!

1162
01:46:22.003 --> 01:46:24.964
We saw him return
in his new body!

1163
01:46:25.089 --> 01:46:26.757
Let us now confess.....

1164
01:46:31.345 --> 01:46:32.847
How do you turn that off?

1165
01:46:33.806 --> 01:46:35.266
I'm not sure.

1166
01:46:35.600 --> 01:46:37.059
Then. what do we do?

1167
01:46:37.727 --> 01:46:40.438
It must be dispersed
with a lightning conductor....

1168
01:46:40.563 --> 01:46:42.023
...but I'm not an engineer.

1169
01:46:43.107 --> 01:46:44.567
I'm sorry.

1170
01:46:45.568 --> 01:46:47.028
Give me all the power.

1171
01:46:49.196 --> 01:46:50.656
What will you do?

1172
01:46:51.198 --> 01:46:53.951
Not sure.
but we gotta try something!

1173
01:47:12.970 --> 01:47:14.472
Hey!

1174
01:47:14.597 --> 01:47:16.098
If you succeed.
I'll say we're the same age.

1175
01:47:16.223 --> 01:47:17.934
If I do. I'll be your big bro!

1176
01:49:02.121 --> 01:49:03.581
Yes!
-If you're done....

1177
01:49:03.706 --> 01:49:05.166
...return the tattoos!

1178
01:49:05.541 --> 01:49:07.001
I'm your big bro now!

1179
01:49:08.002 --> 01:49:09.462
Oh. my.

1180
01:49:10.337 --> 01:49:13.257
Let's hold hands now.
-Hold on.

1181
01:49:13.382 --> 01:49:15.801
Give it to me.
-Hold hands.

1182
01:49:19.638 --> 01:49:21.098
Gotcha!

1183
01:49:40.117 --> 01:49:42.536
Why are you trying to win?

1184
01:49:42.661 --> 01:49:45.456
You losers should follow my orders
and give me what I want!

1185
01:49:45.581 --> 01:49:47.541
Stop it!
-Nine Girl!

1186
01:49:47.666 --> 01:49:49.168
Let go!

1187
01:49:49.502 --> 01:49:50.961
I can't!

1188
01:49:55.841 --> 01:49:57.760
Dad!

1189
01:50:04.975 --> 01:50:06.435
My baby girl!

1190
01:50:06.977 --> 01:50:09.063
Sweetie!
Why are you in a mess?

1191
01:50:09.188 --> 01:50:11.649
Did you fall?
Did someone hit you?

1192
01:50:11.816 --> 01:50:14.276
Who hit my weak. little girl?

1193
01:50:14.401 --> 01:50:16.862
Daddy's so sorry!

1194
01:50:17.029 --> 01:50:20.491
I tried to come sooner.
I'm so sorry.

1195
01:50:20.991 --> 01:50:24.620
Are you okay?
Daddy's so sorry.

1196
01:50:29.333 --> 01:50:30.793
Are you okay?

1197
01:50:31.627 --> 01:50:34.046
Darn young jerk!

1198
01:51:11.709 --> 01:51:13.169
Huh Heel-han.

1199
01:51:14.253 --> 01:51:16.547
Want to be a cult leader?

1200
01:51:26.640 --> 01:51:28.350
I'm going to be a nurse.

1201
01:52:13.646 --> 01:52:15.731
Goddammit.

1202
01:52:23.864 --> 01:52:26.742
I'll get the van. Wait here.

1203
01:52:30.079 --> 01:52:31.538
Oh. no!

1204
01:52:33.749 --> 01:52:36.752
The yogurt must've all gone bad!

1205
01:52:37.670 --> 01:52:39.755
To deliver at night....

1206
01:52:40.172 --> 01:52:44.176
...I had a cart full of yogurt
and diet food.

1207
01:52:45.803 --> 01:52:48.097
Was the parking lot this way?

1208
01:52:49.556 --> 01:52:52.184
Blues Man.
-Bluetooth Man!

1209
01:52:52.309 --> 01:52:53.769
Right.

1210
01:52:54.478 --> 01:52:59.149
How about a song
while we wait for the van?

1211
01:53:00.109 --> 01:53:02.486
What do you want to hear?
I'll just play a song.

1212
01:53:02.611 --> 01:53:04.071
Hey. play that song.

1213
01:53:04.196 --> 01:53:05.656
No way.

1214
01:53:05.823 --> 01:53:07.283
I didn't say what song.

1215
01:53:08.867 --> 01:53:10.703
Battery Man.
-Yes?

1216
01:53:10.828 --> 01:53:13.455
Can you fix this for me later?

1217
01:53:13.580 --> 01:53:15.916
I'll buy some water on the way
and fix it for you.

1218
01:53:16.125 --> 01:53:18.585
Where did I leave the car key?

1219
01:53:19.712 --> 01:53:22.172
Here it is.
Okay.

1220
01:53:22.715 --> 01:53:25.884
How about picking a name
while we wait for the car?

1221
01:53:26.010 --> 01:53:27.553
We picked names last time.

1222
01:53:27.678 --> 01:53:30.806
That's our own names.
We don't have a group name yet.

1223
01:53:30.931 --> 01:53:35.394
In movies. they have names for
a team with superpowers.

1224
01:53:35.519 --> 01:53:36.979
Just choose a name.

1225
01:53:37.396 --> 01:53:40.232
In English or Korean?
-Choose whatever you want.

1226
01:53:40.357 --> 01:53:42.443
Actually. I'm good
at naming things.

1227
01:53:42.568 --> 01:53:44.236
No. I'll just name us.

1228
01:53:44.611 --> 01:53:48.240
You've worked hard.
Just recharge. Battery Man.

1229
01:53:50.701 --> 01:53:55.080
How about a nice. courteous name
like a greeting?

1230
01:53:55.831 --> 01:53:57.791
A name just crossed my mind.....

1231
01:53:57.916 --> 01:54:03.047
There are 5 of us! What's
a greeting of five in English?

1232
01:54:03.297 --> 01:54:05.799
I know what you mean.

1233
01:54:06.717 --> 01:54:10.054
Mister. Do this.
-Right.

1234
01:54:10.346 --> 01:54:15.642
"HI-FIVE"
